    49→  // Generate a laser/plasma shot sound
    50→  generateLaserShot(volume = 0.3): void {
    51→    const ctx = this.getContext();
    52→    const now = ctx.currentTime;
    53→
    54→    // Oscillator for the main tone
    55→    const osc = ctx.createOscillator();
    56→    osc.type = 'sawtooth';
    57→    osc.frequency.setValueAtTime(800, now);

    60→    // High frequency component for "zap" effect
    61→    const oscHigh = ctx.createOscillator();

    63→    oscHigh.frequency.setValueAtTime(2000, now);
    64→    oscHigh.frequency.exponentialRampToValueAtTime(400, now + 0.08);
    65→

    68→    const noiseData = noiseBuffer.getChannelData(0);
    69→    for (let i = 0; i < noiseData.length; i++) {
    70→      noiseData[i] = Math.random() * 2 - 1;
    71→    }
    72→    const noise = ctx.createBufferSource();
    73→    noise.buffer = noiseBuffer;
    74→
    75→    // Filter for noise
    76→    const noiseFilter = ctx.createBiquadFilter();

    81→    // Gain envelopes

    96→    mainGain.connect(ctx.destination);

   233→  // Generate wind/atmospheric sound for drop sequence
   234→  generateDropWind(duration = 1, volume = 0.3): { stop: () => void } {
   235→    const ctx = this.getContext();
   236→    const now = ctx.currentTime;
   237→
   238→    // Brown noise for wind
   239→    const bufferSize = ctx.sampleRate * duration;
   240→    const noiseBuffer = ctx.createBuffer(1, bufferSize, ctx.sampleRate);
   241→    const noiseData = noiseBuffer.getChannelData(0);
   242→    let lastOut = 0;
   243→    for (let i = 0; i < bufferSize; i++) {
   244→      const white = Math.random() * 2 - 1;
   245→      noiseData[i] = (lastOut + 0.02 * white) / 1.02;
   246→      lastOut = noiseData[i];
   247→      noiseData[i] *= 3.5; // Compensate for volume drop
   248→    }
   249→
   250→    const noise = ctx.createBufferSource();
   251→    noise.buffer = noiseBuffer;
   252→    noise.loop = true;
   253→
   254→    // Resonant filter for whistling effect
   255→    const filter = ctx.createBiquadFilter();
   256→    filter.type = 'bandpass';
   257→    filter.frequency.value = 400;
   258→    filter.Q.value = 5;
   259→
   260→    const gain = ctx.createGain();
   261→    gain.gain.setValueAtTime(volume, now);
   262→
   263→    noise.connect(filter);
   264→    filter.connect(gain);
   265→    gain.connect(ctx.destination);
   266→
   267→    noise.start(now);
   268→
   269→    return {
   270→      stop: () => {
   271→        gain.gain.exponentialRampToValueAtTime(0.01, ctx.currentTime + 0.5);
   272→        setTimeout(() => noise.stop(), 600);
   273→      },
   274→    };
   275→  }
   276→
   277→  // Generate thrust/engine sound
   278→  generateThrustSound(volume = 0.25): { stop: () => void } {
   279→    const ctx = this.getContext();
   280→    const now = ctx.currentTime;
   281→

   290→
   291→    // Filter

   294→    filter.frequency.value = 200;
   295→
   296→    // LFO for wobble
   297→    const lfo = ctx.createOscillator();
   298→    lfo.frequency.value = 8;
   299→    const lfoGain = ctx.createGain();
   300→    lfoGain.gain.value = 20;
   301→    lfo.connect(lfoGain);
   302→    lfoGain.connect(osc1.frequency);
   303→
   304→    const gain = ctx.createGain();
   305→    gain.gain.setValueAtTime(0, now);
   306→    gain.gain.linearRampToValueAtTime(volume, now + 0.3);
   307→
   308→    osc1.connect(filter);
   309→    osc2.connect(filter);
   310→    filter.connect(gain);
   311→    gain.connect(ctx.destination);
   312→
   313→    osc1.start(now);
   314→    osc2.start(now);
   315→    lfo.start(now);
   316→

   318→      stop: () => {

   321→          osc1.stop();
   322→          osc2.stop();

   328→
   329→  // Notification/comms beep
   330→  generateNotificationBeep(volume = 0.2): void {
   331→    const ctx = this.getContext();
   332→    const now = ctx.currentTime;
   333→
   334→    // Two-tone beep
   335→    const osc = ctx.createOscillator();
   336→    osc.type = 'sine';
   337→    osc.frequency.setValueAtTime(880, now);
   338→    osc.frequency.setValueAtTime(1100, now + 0.08);
   339→
   340→    const gain = ctx.createGain();
   341→    gain.gain.setValueAtTime(0, now);
   342→    gain.gain.linearRampToValueAtTime(volume, now + 0.01);
   343→    gain.gain.setValueAtTime(volume, now + 0.07);
   344→    gain.gain.linearRampToValueAtTime(volume * 0.6, now + 0.08);
   345→    gain.gain.linearRampToValueAtTime(volume * 0.6, now + 0.15);
   346→    gain.gain.linearRampToValueAtTime(0, now + 0.2);
   347→
   348→    osc.connect(gain);
   349→    gain.connect(ctx.destination);
   350→
   351→    osc.start(now);
   352→    osc.stop(now + 0.25);
   353→  }
   354→
   355→  dispose(): void {
   356→    if (this.audioContext) {
   357→      this.audioContext.close();
   358→      this.audioContext = null;
   359→    }
   360→  }
   361→}
   362→
   363→// Main Audio Manager class
   364→export class AudioManager {
   365→  private scene: Scene | null = null;
   366→  private sounds: Map<string, Sound> = new Map();
   367→  private proceduralAudio: ProceduralAudio;
   368→
   369→  private masterVolume = 1.0;
   370→  private sfxVolume = 0.7;
   371→  private musicVolume = 0.5;
   372→
   373→  private isMuted = false;
   374→  private currentMusic: Sound | null = null;
   375→  private activeLoops: Map<string, { stop: () => void }> = new Map();
   376→
   377→  constructor() {
   378→    this.proceduralAudio = new ProceduralAudio();
   379→  }
   380→
   381→  initialize(scene: Scene): void {
   382→    this.scene = scene;
   383→  }
   384→
   385→  // Play a sound effect
   386→  play(effect: SoundEffect, options?: { volume?: number; position?: Vector3 }): void {
   387→    if (this.isMuted) return;
   388→    
   389→    // Check if audio context is available
   390→    if (!this.proceduralAudio || !this.proceduralAudio['audioContext']) {
   391→        // Fallback or ignore if audio not supported/initialized
   392→        // Ideally we would check `this.proceduralAudio.getContext()` but it's private
   393→        // For now, we assume it's safe if not muted, but let's add a try-catch for safety
   394→    }
   395→
   396→    const volume = (options?.volume ?? 1) * this.sfxVolume * this.masterVolume;
   397→
   398→    try {
   399→      // Use procedural audio for most effects (no external files needed)
   400→      switch (effect) {
   401→        case 'weapon_fire':
   402→          this.proceduralAudio.generateLaserShot(volume);
   403→          break;
   404→        case 'hit_marker':
   405→          this.proceduralAudio.generateHitMarker(volume);
   406→          break;
   407→        case 'player_damage':
   408→          this.proceduralAudio.generateDamage(volume);
   409→          break;
   410→        case 'footstep':
   411→          this.proceduralAudio.generateFootstep(volume);
   412→          break;
   413→        case 'ui_click':
   414→          this.proceduralAudio.generateUIClick(volume);
   415→          break;
   416→        case 'notification':
   417→        case 'comms_open':
   418→          this.proceduralAudio.generateNotificationBeep(volume);
   419→          break;
   420→        case 'weapon_reload':
   421→        case 'enemy_death':
   422→        case 'jump':
   423→        case 'land':
   424→        case 'ambient_wind':
   425→        case 'ui_hover':
   426→        case 'drop_impact':
   427→        case 'comms_close':
   428→        case 'door_open':
   429→        case 'airlock':
   430→        case 'drop_wind':
   431→        case 'drop_thrust':
   432→          // Placeholder for effects not yet implemented procedurally
   433→          // In a full implementation, these would have their own generators
   434→          // or load from files. For now, silence is better than a crash.
   435→          break;
   436→      }
   437→    } catch (e) {
   438→      console.warn('Audio play failed', e);
   439→    }
   440→  }
   441→
   442→  // Start a looping sound
   443→  startLoop(effect: 'drop_wind' | 'drop_thrust', volume = 1): void {
   444→    if (this.isMuted) return;
   445→    if (this.activeLoops.has(effect)) return;
   446→
   447→    try {
   448→      const vol = volume * this.sfxVolume * this.masterVolume;
   449→
   450→      let loop: { stop: () => void };
   451→      switch (effect) {
   452→        case 'drop_wind':
   453→          loop = this.proceduralAudio.generateDropWind(5, vol);
   454→          break;
   455→        case 'drop_thrust':
   456→          loop = this.proceduralAudio.generateThrustSound(vol);
   457→          break;
   458→        default:
   459→          return;
   460→      }
   461→
   462→      this.activeLoops.set(effect, loop);
   463→    } catch (e) {
   464→        console.warn('Audio loop failed', e);
   465→    }
   466→  }
   467→
   468→  // Stop a looping sound
   469→  stopLoop(effect: string): void {
   470→    const loop = this.activeLoops.get(effect);
   471→    if (loop) {
   472→      loop.stop();
   473→      this.activeLoops.delete(effect);
   474→    }
   475→  }
   476→
   477→  // Stop all loops
   478→  stopAllLoops(): void {
   479→    for (const [key, loop] of this.activeLoops) {
   480→      loop.stop();
   481→    }
   482→    this.activeLoops.clear();
   483→  }
   484→
   485→  // Volume controls
   486→  setMasterVolume(volume: number): void {
   487→    this.masterVolume = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, volume));
   488→  }
   489→
   490→  setSFXVolume(volume: number): void {
   491→    this.sfxVolume = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, volume));
   492→  }
   493→
   494→  setMusicVolume(volume: number): void {
   495→    this.musicVolume = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, volume));
   496→    if (this.currentMusic) {
   497→      this.currentMusic.setVolume(this.musicVolume * this.masterVolume);
   498→    }
   499→  }
   500→
   501→  mute(): void {
   502→    this.isMuted = true;
   503→    this.stopAllLoops();
   504→    if (this.currentMusic) {
   505→      this.currentMusic.pause();
   506→    }
   507→  }
   508→
   509→  unmute(): void {
   510→    this.isMuted = false;
   511→    if (this.currentMusic) {
   512→      this.currentMusic.play();
   513→    }
   514→  }
   515→
   516→  toggleMute(): boolean {
   517→    if (this.isMuted) {
   518→      this.unmute();
   519→    } else {
   520→      this.mute();
   521→    }
   522→    return this.isMuted;
   523→  }
   524→
   525→  dispose(): void {
   526→    this.stopAllLoops();
   527→
   528→    for (const sound of this.sounds.values()) {
   529→      sound.dispose();
   530→    }
   531→    this.sounds.clear();
   532→
   533→    if (this.currentMusic) {
   534→      this.currentMusic.dispose();
   535→      this.currentMusic = null;
   536→    }
   537→
   538→    this.proceduralAudio.dispose();
   539→  }
   540→}
   541→
   542→// Singleton instance
   543→let audioManagerInstance: AudioManager | null = null;
   544→
   545→export function getAudioManager(): AudioManager {
   546→  if (!audioManagerInstance) {
   547→    audioManagerInstance = new AudioManager();
   548→  }
   549→  return audioManagerInstance;
   550→}
   551→
   552→export function disposeAudioManager(): void {
   553→  if (audioManagerInstance) {
   554→    audioManagerInstance.dispose();
   555→    audioManagerInstance = null;
   556→  }
   557→}
   558→

     1→import { Texture } from '@babylonjs/core/Materials/Textures/texture';
     2→import type { Scene } from '@babylonjs/core/scene';
     3→
     4→export interface LoadingProgress {
     5→  stage: string;
     6→  progress: number;
     7→  detail?: string;
     8→}
     9→
    10→export interface AssetManifest {
    11→  textures: { name: string; url: string }[];
    12→  // Add more asset types as needed: models, sounds, etc.
    13→}
    14→
    15→// Default manifest - add actual game assets here
    16→export const DEFAULT_MANIFEST: AssetManifest = {
    17→  textures: [{ name: 'rock', url: 'https://assets.babylonjs.com/textures/rock.png' }],
    18→};
    19→
    20→export class AssetLoader {
    21→  private scene: Scene;
    22→  private loadedAssets: Map<string, unknown> = new Map();
    23→  private progressCallback?: (progress: LoadingProgress) => void;
    24→
    25→  constructor(scene: Scene) {
    26→    this.scene = scene;
    27→  }
    28→
    29→  onProgress(callback: (progress: LoadingProgress) => void): void {
    30→    this.progressCallback = callback;
    31→  }
    32→
    33→  private updateProgress(stage: string, progress: number, detail?: string): void {
    34→    this.progressCallback?.({ stage, progress, detail });
    35→  }
    36→
    37→  async loadAll(manifest: AssetManifest = DEFAULT_MANIFEST): Promise<void> {
    38→    const totalAssets = manifest.textures.length;
    39→    let loadedCount = 0;
    40→
    41→    this.updateProgress('INITIALIZING SYSTEMS', 0);
    42→
    43→    // Load textures
    44→    if (manifest.textures.length > 0) {
    45→      this.updateProgress('LOADING TEXTURES', 5);
    46→
    47→      for (const textureInfo of manifest.textures) {
    48→        try {
    49→          const texture = await this.loadTexture(textureInfo.name, textureInfo.url);
    50→          this.loadedAssets.set(`texture:${textureInfo.name}`, texture);
    51→          loadedCount++;
    52→          const progress = 5 + (loadedCount / totalAssets) * 60;
    53→          this.updateProgress('LOADING TEXTURES', progress, textureInfo.name);
    54→        } catch (error) {
    55→          console.warn(`Failed to load texture ${textureInfo.name}:`, error);
    56→          loadedCount++;
    57→        }
    58→      }
    59→    }
    60→
    61→    this.updateProgress('COMPILING SHADERS', 70);
    62→    // Shaders compile on first use, but we can trigger compilation here
    63→    await this.waitFrame();
    64→
    65→    this.updateProgress('INITIALIZING PHYSICS', 80);
    66→    await this.waitFrame();
    67→
    68→    this.updateProgress('PREPARING SCENE', 90);
    69→    await this.waitFrame();
    70→
    71→    this.updateProgress('SYSTEMS ONLINE', 100);
    72→  }
    73→
    74→  private loadTexture(name: string, url: string): Promise<Texture> {
    75→    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    76→      const texture = new Texture(
    77→        url,
    78→        this.scene,
    79→        false, // noMipmap
    80→        true, // invertY
    81→        Texture.TRILINEAR_SAMPLINGMODE,
    82→        () => resolve(texture),
    83→        (message, exception) => reject(exception || new Error(message || 'Failed to load texture'))
    84→      );
    85→    });
    86→  }
    87→
    88→  private waitFrame(): Promise<void> {
    89→    return new Promise((resolve) => requestAnimationFrame(() => resolve()));
    90→  }
    91→
    92→  getTexture(name: string): Texture | undefined {
    93→    return this.loadedAssets.get(`texture:${name}`) as Texture | undefined;
    94→  }
    95→
    96→  dispose(): void {
    97→    for (const [key, asset] of this.loadedAssets) {
    98→      if (key.startsWith('texture:') && asset instanceof Texture) {
    99→        asset.dispose();
   100→      }
   101→    }
   102→    this.loadedAssets.clear();
   103→  }
   104→}
   105→

     1→# STELLAR DESCENT: PROXIMA BREACH — Complete Lore Bible
     2→
     3→This document contains the complete narrative, world-building, characters, and story content for the game. It serves as the canonical source for all story-related decisions.
     4→
     5→---
     6→
     7→## Setting
     8→
     9→### The Year: 3147 CE
    10→
    11→One thousand years in the future, humanity has spread beyond Earth. The Solar System is fully colonized, and the first interstellar missions have reached Alpha Centauri.
    12→
    13→### The Terran Expansion Authority (TEA)
    14→
    15→The governing body overseeing human expansion beyond the Solar System. Part military, part colonial administration, the TEA manages:
    16→- Interstellar colonization missions
    17→- Military protection of colonies
    18→- Resource extraction rights
    19→- Terraforming operations
    20→
    21→### Faster-Than-Light Travel
    22→
    23→FTL travel exists but is expensive and limited. Colony ships travel at ~0.3c using Alcubierre-derived warp technology. The journey to Proxima Centauri takes approximately 14 years.
    24→
    25→### ANCHOR Stations
    26→
    27→Mobile deployment platforms positioned in orbit above target worlds. These massive stations (2+ km in length) serve as:
    28→- Staging areas for ground operations
    29→- Command and control centers
    30→- Housing for 4,000+ personnel
    31→- Drop pod launch platforms
    32→- Medical and R&R facilities
    33→
    34→---
    35→
    36→## Location: Proxima Centauri b
    37→
    38→### Astronomical Data
    39→
    40→| Property | Value |
    41→| :--- | :--- |
    42→| Designation | PCb-7 "Kepler's Promise" |
    43→| Star | Proxima Centauri (Red Dwarf, M5.5Ve) |
    44→| Distance from Earth | 4.24 light years |
    45→| Orbital Period | 11.2 Earth days |
    46→| Mass | ~1.3 Earth masses |
    47→| Gravity | ~1.1g |
    48→| Atmosphere | Thin, primarily CO2/N2, requires respirator |
    49→
    50→### Environment
    51→
    52→## Surface Conditions
    53→- Rocky, desert terrain
    54→- Large canyon systems
    55→- Sparse vegetation (extremophile plants)
    56→- Frequent dust storms
    57→- Temperature extremes (-40°C to +30°C)
    58→
    59→## Lighting
    60→- Proxima Centauri is a red dwarf
    61→- ~65% of Earth's solar radiation
    62→- Perpetual "sunset" quality to light
    63→- High UV output (dangerous without protection)
    64→- Harsh shadows due to point light source
    65→
    66→## Geography
    67→- Northern Hemisphere: Canyon lands (FOB Delta location)
    68→- Equatorial Region: Rocky desert (player drop zone)
    69→- Southern Hemisphere: Ice fields (unexplored)
    70→
    71→### Indigenous Life
    72→
    73→Prior to Vanguard's mission, orbital surveys detected:
    74→- Extremophile bacteria
    75→- Simple plant analogs
    76→- No detected fauna
    77→
    78→**The surveys were wrong.**
    79→
    80→---
    81→
    82→## The Enemy: Strain-X / "Chitin"
    83→
    84→### Discovery
    85→
    86→The Chitin were not detected during orbital surveys because:
    87→1. They live deep underground
    88→2. Their hives are shielded by rock
    89→3. They were in hibernation cycles
    90→4. Seismic activity from mining operations awakened them
    91→
    92→### Biology
    93→
    94→**Classification**: Insectoid hive species
    95→
    96→**Physical Characteristics**
    97→- Chitinous exoskeleton (hence the nickname)
    98→- Six limbs (four legs, two arms)
    99→- Compound eyes sensitive to infrared
   100→- Bioluminescent markings
   101→- Size varies by caste (0.5m to 4m)
   102→
   103→**Reproduction**
   104→- Single queen per hive
   105→- Queen produces all eggs
   106→- Workers and soldiers are sterile
   107→- New queens budded during hive expansion
   108→
   109→**Communication**
   110→- Pheromone-based for basic signals
   111→- Hive mind connection to queen
   112→- Queen's death causes temporary disorientation
   113→
   114→### Variants
   115→
   116→#### Drones
   117→- **Size**: 0.5-0.8m
   118→- **Health**: 30 HP
   119→- **Damage**: 5
   120→- **Behavior**: Scouts and swarmers
   121→- **Color**: Purple-black
   122→- **Notes**: Fast but fragile, attack in groups of 5-10
   123→
   124→#### Grunts (Soldiers)
   125→- **Size**: 1.5-1.8m
   126→- **Health**: 100 HP
   127→- **Damage**: 15
   128→- **Behavior**: Main combat unit
   129→- **Color**: Dark gray-green
   130→- **Notes**: Standard enemy, balanced stats
   131→
   132→#### Brutes
   133→- **Size**: 2.5-3m
   134→- **Health**: 200 HP
   135→- **Damage**: 25
   136→- **Behavior**: Heavy assault
   137→- **Color**: Deep red-brown
   138→- **Notes**: Slow but devastating, can charge
   139→
   140→#### Spitters

   142→- **Health**: 50 HP
   143→- **Damage**: 40 (acid)
   144→- **Behavior**: Ranged support
   145→- **Color**: Pale green
   146→- **Notes**: Weak but dangerous at range
   147→
   148→#### Queen
   149→- **Size**: 4m+
   150→- **Health**: 5000 HP
   151→- **Damage**: 60 (melee), spawns minions
   152→- **Behavior**: Hive controller
   153→- **Color**: Iridescent purple

    24→// The Anchor Station level - tutorial introduction to the game

    27→  private engine: Engine;

    29→

    65→  constructor(
    66→    scene: Scene,

    72→    this.engine = engine;

    81→    this.boundKeyUp = this.handleKeyUp.bind(this);

    83→    this.boundClick = this.handleClick.bind(this);
    84→  }
    85→
    86→  private createCamera(): UniversalCamera {
    87→    const camera = new UniversalCamera(
    88→      'stationCamera',
    89→      new Vector3(0, 1.7, 0), // Standing height at start
    90→      this.scene
    91→    );
    92→
    93→    camera.rotation.y = this.rotationY;
    94→    camera.minZ = 0.1;
    95→    camera.maxZ = 500;
    96→    // Proper FPS FOV - not too wide, not too narrow
    97→    camera.fov = 1.2; // ~69 degrees - good for FPS
    98→
    99→    // Clear default inputs - we handle manually
   100→    camera.inputs.clear();
   101→
   102→    return camera;
   103→  }
   104→
   105→  initialize(): void {
   106→    // Create station environment
   107→    this.environment = createStationEnvironment(this.scene);
   108→
   109→    // Set this camera as active
   110→    this.scene.activeCamera = this.camera;
   111→
   112→    // Create objective marker
   113→    this.objectiveMarker = MeshBuilder.CreateCylinder(
   114→      'objectiveMarker',
   115→      {
   116→        height: 0.1,
   117→        diameter: 1.5,
   118→        tessellation: 16,
   119→      },
   120→      this.scene
   121→    );
   122→    const markerMat = new StandardMaterial('markerMat', this.scene);
   123→    markerMat.emissiveColor = Color3.FromHexString('#FFD700');
   124→    markerMat.alpha = 0.4;
   125→    this.objectiveMarker.material = markerMat;
   126→    this.objectiveMarker.isVisible = false;
   127→
   128→    // Create interaction prompt (HTML overlay)
   129→    this.createInteractionPrompt();
   130→
   131→    // Setup controls
   132→    this.setupControls();
   133→
   134→    // Start tutorial with sequence handlers
   135→    this.tutorialManager.start({
   136→      onStepChange: (step) => {
   137→        // Update objective marker position
   138→        const target = this.tutorialManager.getCurrentObjectiveTarget();
   139→        if (target && this.objectiveMarker) {
   140→          this.objectiveMarker.position = target.clone();
   141→          this.objectiveMarker.position.y = 0.1;
   142→          this.objectiveMarker.isVisible = true;
   143→        } else if (this.objectiveMarker) {
   144→          this.objectiveMarker.isVisible = false;
   145→        }
   146→      },
   147→      onCommsMessage: (message) => {
   148→        this.callbacks.onCommsMessage(message);
   149→      },
   150→      onObjectiveUpdate: (title, instructions) => {
   151→        this.callbacks.onObjectiveUpdate(title, instructions);
   152→      },
   153→      onTriggerSequence: (sequence) => {
   154→        this.handleSequence(sequence);
   155→      },
   156→      onComplete: () => {
   157→        this.callbacks.onTutorialComplete();
   158→      },
   159→    });
   160→
   161→    this.isActive = true;
   162→    this.callbacks.onNotification('ANCHOR STATION PROMETHEUS', 3000);
   163→  }
   164→
   165→  private createInteractionPrompt(): void {
   166→    this.interactionPrompt = document.createElement('div');
   167→    this.interactionPrompt.className = styles.interactionPrompt;
   168→    
   169→    const key = document.createElement('div');
   170→    key.className = styles.promptKey;
   171→    key.textContent = 'E';
   172→    
   173→    const text = document.createElement('div');
   174→    text.className = styles.promptText;
   175→    text.textContent = 'INTERACT';
   176→    
   177→    this.interactionPrompt.appendChild(key);
   178→    this.interactionPrompt.appendChild(text);
   179→
   180→    document.body.appendChild(this.interactionPrompt);
   181→  }
   182→
   183→  private handleSequence(sequence: string): void {
   184→    if (!this.environment) return;
   185→
   186→    switch (sequence) {
   187→      case 'equip_suit':
   188→        this.suitEquipped = true;
   189→        this.environment.playEquipSuit(() => {
   190→          this.callbacks.onNotification('EVA SUIT EQUIPPED', 2000);
   191→        });
   192→        break;
   193→
   194→      case 'depressurize':
   195→        this.environment.playDepressurize(() => {
   196→          // Depressurization complete
   197→        });
   198→        break;
   199→
   200→      case 'open_bay_doors':
   201→        this.environment.playOpenBayDoors(() => {
   202→          this.callbacks.onNotification('BAY DOORS OPEN', 2000);
   203→        });
   204→        break;
   205→
   206→      case 'enter_pod':
   207→        this.environment.playEnterPod(() => {
   208→          // Lock player in pod position
   209→          this.camera.position.set(0, 1.7, -47);
   210→          this.rotationY = Math.PI; // Face the opening
   211→        });
   212→        break;
   213→
   214→      case 'launch':
   215→        this.environment.playLaunch(() => {
   216→          // Tutorial complete - transition to HALO drop
   217→        });
   218→        break;
   219→
   220→      case 'start_calibration':
   221→        this.targetsHit = 0;
   222→        this.callbacks.onCalibrationStart?.();
   223→        this.environment.startCalibration({
   224→          onTargetHit: (targetIndex) => {
   225→            this.targetsHit++;
   226→            this.callbacks.onNotification(`TARGET ${this.targetsHit}/${this.totalTargets}`, 800);
   227→          },
   228→          onAllTargetsHit: () => {
   229→            this.callbacks.onCalibrationEnd?.();
   230→            this.callbacks.onNotification('CALIBRATION COMPLETE', 1500);
   231→            this.tutorialManager.onShootingRangeComplete();
   232→          },
   233→        });
   234→        break;
   235→    }
   236→  }
   237→
   238→  private handleKeyDown(e: KeyboardEvent): void {
   239→    this.keysPressed.add(e.code);
   240→
   241→    // Handle interaction
   242→    if (e.code === 'KeyE' && this.tutorialManager.isInteractStep()) {
   243→      this.tryInteract();
   244→    }
   245→  }
   246→
   247→  private handleKeyUp(e: KeyboardEvent): void {
   248→    this.keysPressed.delete(e.code);
   249→  }
   250→
   251→  private handleMouseMove(e: MouseEvent): void {
   252→    // Mouse look - turn the player when pointer is locked
   253→    if (document.pointerLockElement === this.canvas) {
   254→      const sensitivity = 0.002;
   255→      this.rotationY += e.movementX * sensitivity;
   256→      this.rotationX -= e.movementY * sensitivity;
   257→      this.rotationX = Math.max(-Math.PI / 2.2, Math.min(Math.PI / 2.2, this.rotationX));
   258→    }
   259→  }
   260→
   261→  private handleClick(): void {
   262→    if (this.isActive) {
   263→      // If calibration is active and pointer is locked, try to shoot
   264→      if (this.environment?.isCalibrationActive() && document.pointerLockElement === this.canvas) {
   265→        this.tryShoot();
   266→        return;
   267→      }
   268→
   269→      // If showing interaction prompt, try to interact
   270→      if (this.showingPrompt && this.tutorialManager.isInteractStep()) {
   271→        this.tryInteract();
   272→      } else {
   273→        this.canvas.requestPointerLock();
   274→      }
   275→    }
   276→  }
   277→
   278→  private tryShoot(): void {
   279→    if (!this.environment?.isCalibrationActive()) return;
   280→
   281→    // Get ray from camera center
   282→    const rayOrigin = this.camera.position.clone();
   283→    const rayDirection = this.camera.getDirection(Vector3.Forward());
   284→
   285→    // Check for target hit
   286→    this.environment.checkTargetHit(rayOrigin, rayDirection);
   287→  }
   288→
   289→  private tryInteract(): void {
   290→    if (this.tutorialManager.tryInteract(this.camera.position)) {
   291→      this.hideInteractionPrompt();
   292→    }
   293→  }
   294→
   295→  private showInteractionPrompt(): void {
   296→    if (this.interactionPrompt && !this.showingPrompt) {
   297→      this.interactionPrompt.style.display = 'flex';
   298→      this.showingPrompt = true;
   299→    }
   300→  }
   301→
   302→  private hideInteractionPrompt(): void {
   303→    if (this.interactionPrompt && this.showingPrompt) {
   304→      this.interactionPrompt.style.display = 'none';
   305→      this.showingPrompt = false;
   306→    }
   307→  }
   308→
   309→  private setupControls(): void {
   310→    window.addEventListener('keydown', this.boundKeyDown);
   311→    window.addEventListener('keyup', this.boundKeyUp);
   312→    document.addEventListener('mousemove', this.boundMouseMove);
   313→    this.canvas.addEventListener('click', this.boundClick);
   314→  }
   315→
   316→  private removeControls(): void {
   317→    window.removeEventListener('keydown', this.boundKeyDown);
   318→    window.removeEventListener('keyup', this.boundKeyUp);
   319→    document.removeEventListener('mousemove', this.boundMouseMove);
   320→    this.canvas.removeEventListener('click', this.boundClick);
   321→  }
   322→
   323→  setTouchInput(input: TouchInput | null): void {
   324→    this.touchInput = input;
   325→  }
   326→
   327→  update(deltaTime: number): void {
   328→    if (!this.isActive) return;
   329→
   330→    // Apply camera rotation - camera follows player turn
   331→    this.camera.rotation.x = this.rotationX;
   332→    this.camera.rotation.y = this.rotationY;
   333→
   334→    // Movement
   335→    const moveDir = Vector3.Zero();
   336→
   337→    if (this.touchInput) {
   338→      // Touch input - movement from left joystick
   339→      const movement = this.touchInput.movement;
   340→      if (Math.abs(movement.x) > 0.1 || Math.abs(movement.y) > 0.1) {
   341→        moveDir.addInPlace(this.camera.getDirection(Vector3.Forward()).scale(movement.y));
   342→        moveDir.addInPlace(this.camera.getDirection(Vector3.Right()).scale(movement.x));
   343→      }
   344→
   345→      // Touch look from screen drag
   346→      const look = this.touchInput.look;
   347→      if (Math.abs(look.x) > 0.0001 || Math.abs(look.y) > 0.0001) {
   348→        this.rotationY += look.x;
   349→        this.rotationX -= look.y;
   350→        this.rotationX = Math.max(-Math.PI / 2.2, Math.min(Math.PI / 2.2, this.rotationX));
   351→      }
   352→    } else {
   353→      // Keyboard
   354→      if (this.keysPressed.has('KeyW')) {
   355→        moveDir.addInPlace(this.camera.getDirection(Vector3.Forward()));
   356→      }
   357→      if (this.keysPressed.has('KeyS')) {
   358→        moveDir.addInPlace(this.camera.getDirection(Vector3.Backward()));
   359→      }
   360→      if (this.keysPressed.has('KeyA')) {
   361→        moveDir.addInPlace(this.camera.getDirection(Vector3.Left()));
   362→      }
   363→      if (this.keysPressed.has('KeyD')) {
   364→        moveDir.addInPlace(this.camera.getDirection(Vector3.Right()));
   365→      }
   366→    }
   367→
   368→    // Apply movement
   369→    if (moveDir.length() > 0) {
   370→      moveDir.normalize();
   371→      moveDir.y = 0;
   372→      moveDir.scaleInPlace(this.moveSpeed * deltaTime);
   373→      this.camera.position.addInPlace(moveDir);
   374→    }
   375→
   376→    // Keep at standing height
   377→    this.camera.position.y = 1.7;
   378→
   379→    // Clamp to corridor bounds
   380→    const corridorHalfWidth = 4.5;
   381→    const corridorEnd = -53;
   382→    this.camera.position.x = Math.max(
   383→      -corridorHalfWidth,
   384→      Math.min(corridorHalfWidth, this.camera.position.x)
   385→    );
   386→    this.camera.position.z = Math.max(corridorEnd, Math.min(2, this.camera.position.z));
   387→
   388→    // Check tutorial objectives
   389→    const lookDir = this.camera.getDirection(Vector3.Forward());
   390→    this.tutorialManager.checkObjective(this.camera.position, lookDir);
   391→
   392→    // Show/hide interaction prompt
   393→    if (this.tutorialManager.canPlayerInteract(this.camera.position)) {
   394→      this.showInteractionPrompt();
   395→    } else {
   396→      this.hideInteractionPrompt();
   397→    }
   398→
   399→    // Animate objective marker
   400→    if (this.objectiveMarker?.isVisible) {
   401→      this.objectiveMarker.rotation.y += deltaTime * 2;
   402→      // Pulse alpha
   403→      const pulse = 0.3 + Math.sin(performance.now() * 0.003) * 0.15;
   404→      (this.objectiveMarker.material as StandardMaterial).alpha = pulse;
   405→    }
   406→  }
   407→
   408→  // Called when player dismisses comms
   409→  onCommsDismissed(): void {
   410→    this.tutorialManager.onCommsDismissed();
   411→  }
   412→
   413→  skip(): void {
   414→    this.tutorialManager.skip();
   415→  }
   416→
   417→  getCamera(): UniversalCamera {
   418→    return this.camera;
   419→  }
   420→
   421→  dispose(): void {
   422→    this.isActive = false;
   423→    this.removeControls();
   424→    this.tutorialManager.dispose();
   425→    this.environment?.dispose();
   426→    this.objectiveMarker?.dispose();
   427→    this.camera.dispose();
   428→
   429→    // Remove interaction prompt
   430→    if (this.interactionPrompt && this.interactionPrompt.parentNode) {
   431→      this.interactionPrompt.parentNode.removeChild(this.interactionPrompt);
   432→    }
   433→  }
   434→}

    40→// Create the space base environment - corridors, pipes, perspex windows
    41→export function createStationEnvironment(scene: Scene): StationEnvironment {
    42→  const root = new TransformNode('anchorStation', scene);
    43→  const materials = createStationMaterials(scene);
    44→  const lights: PointLight[] = [];
    45→  const allMeshes: Mesh[] = [];
    46→
    47→  // Corridor dimensions - longer to accommodate hangar bay
    48→  const prepBayLength = 25;
    49→  const hangarLength = 30;
    50→  const totalLength = prepBayLength + hangarLength;
    51→  const corridorWidth = 10;
    52→  const corridorHeight = 6;
    53→
    54→  // === FLOOR ===
    55→  const floor = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
    56→    'floor',
    57→    {
    58→      width: corridorWidth,
    59→      height: 0.3,
    60→      depth: totalLength,
    61→    },
    62→    scene
    63→  );
    64→  floor.position.y = -0.15;
    65→  floor.position.z = -totalLength / 2;
    66→  floor.material = materials.get('floor')!;
    67→  floor.parent = root;
    68→  allMeshes.push(floor);
    69→
    70→  // Floor grating pattern
    71→  for (let z = 2; z < totalLength - 5; z += 2.5) {
    72→    for (let x = -corridorWidth / 2 + 1.5; x < corridorWidth / 2 - 1; x += 2.5) {
    73→      const grate = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
    74→        'grate',
    75→        {
    76→          width: 2,
    77→          height: 0.08,
    78→          depth: 2,
    79→        },
    80→        scene
    81→      );
    82→      grate.position.set(x, 0.02, -z);
    83→      grate.material = materials.get('hull')!;
    84→      grate.parent = root;
    85→      allMeshes.push(grate);
    86→    }
    87→  }
    88→
    89→  // Guide line on floor
    90→  const guideLine = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
    91→    'guideLine',
    92→    {
    93→      width: 0.25,
    94→      height: 0.04,
    95→      depth: totalLength - 12,
    96→    },
    97→    scene
    98→  );
    99→  guideLine.position.set(0, 0.025, -totalLength / 2 + 4);
   100→  guideLine.material = materials.get('guide')!;
   101→  guideLine.parent = root;
   102→  allMeshes.push(guideLine);
   103→
   104→  // === WALLS - PREP BAY SECTION ===
   105→  for (let side = -1; side <= 1; side += 2) {
   106→    // Lower wall section
   107→    const lowerWall = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
   108→      'lowerWall',
   109→      {
   110→        width: 0.4,
   111→        height: 2,
   112→        depth: prepBayLength,
   113→      },
   114→      scene
   115→    );
   116→    lowerWall.position.set(side * (corridorWidth / 2 + 0.2), 1, -prepBayLength / 2);
   117→    lowerWall.material = materials.get('hull')!;
   118→    lowerWall.parent = root;
   119→    allMeshes.push(lowerWall);
   120→
   121→    // Upper wall section
   122→    const upperWall = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
   123→      'upperWall',
   124→      {
   125→        width: 0.4,
   126→        height: 1.5,
   127→        depth: prepBayLength,
   128→      },
   129→      scene
   130→    );
   131→    upperWall.position.set(
   132→      side * (corridorWidth / 2 + 0.2),
   133→      corridorHeight - 0.75,
   134→      -prepBayLength / 2
   135→    );
   136→    upperWall.material = materials.get('hull')!;
   137→    upperWall.parent = root;
   138→    allMeshes.push(upperWall);
   139→
   140→    // Windows in prep bay
   141→    for (let z = 8; z < prepBayLength - 5; z += 8) {
   142→      const frame = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
   143→        'windowFrame',
   144→        {
   145→          width: 0.5,
   146→          height: 2.5,
   147→          depth: 6,
   148→        },
   149→        scene
   150→      );
   151→      frame.position.set(side * (corridorWidth / 2 + 0.1), 3.25, -z);
   152→      frame.material = materials.get('windowFrame')!;
   153→      frame.parent = root;
   154→      allMeshes.push(frame);
   155→
   156→      const glass = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
   157→        'window',
   158→        {
   159→          width: 0.1,
   160→          height: 2.2,
   161→          depth: 5.5,
   162→        },
   163→        scene
   164→      );
   165→      glass.position.set(side * (corridorWidth / 2 - 0.05), 3.25, -z);
   166→      glass.material = materials.get('window')!;
   167→      glass.parent = root;
   168→      allMeshes.push(glass);
   169→    }
   170→  }
   171→
   172→  // === EQUIPMENT RACK ===
   173→  const equipmentRackContainer = new TransformNode('equipmentRackContainer', scene);
   174→  equipmentRackContainer.position.set(-3.5, 0, -18);
   175→  equipmentRackContainer.parent = root;
   176→
   177→  // Rack frame
   178→  const rackFrame = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
   179→    'rackFrame',
   180→    {
   181→      width: 2,
   182→      height: 2.5,
   183→      depth: 0.5,
   184→    },
   185→    scene
   186→  );
   187→  rackFrame.position.y = 1.25;
   188→  rackFrame.material = materials.get('hull')!;
   189→  rackFrame.parent = equipmentRackContainer;
   190→  allMeshes.push(rackFrame);
   191→
   192→  // Suit silhouette on rack
   193→  const suitBody = MeshBuilder.CreateCapsule(
   194→    'suitBody',
   195→    {
   196→      height: 1.6,
   197→      radius: 0.3,
   198→    },
   199→    scene
   200→  );
   201→  suitBody.position.set(0, 1.3, 0.1);
   202→  suitBody.material = materials.get('pod')!;
   203→  suitBody.parent = equipmentRackContainer;
   204→  allMeshes.push(suitBody);
   205→
   206→  // Suit helmet
   207→  const suitHelmet = MeshBuilder.CreateSphere(
   208→    'suitHelmet',
   209→    {
   210→      diameter: 0.5,
   211→      segments: 12,
   212→    },
   213→    scene
   214→  );
   215→  suitHelmet.position.set(0, 2.2, 0.1);
   216→  suitHelmet.material = materials.get('pod')!;
   217→  suitHelmet.parent = equipmentRackContainer;
   218→  allMeshes.push(suitHelmet);
   219→
   220→  // Interaction indicator light
   221→  const rackLight = MeshBuilder.CreateSphere(
   222→    'rackLight',
   223→    {
   224→      diameter: 0.15,
   225→    },
   226→    scene
   227→  );
   228→  rackLight.position.set(0, 2.6, 0.3);
   229→  rackLight.material = materials.get('active')!;
   230→  rackLight.parent = equipmentRackContainer;
   231→  allMeshes.push(rackLight);
   232→
   233→  // Pulsing animation for rack light
   234→  const rackPulse = new Animation(
   235→    'rackPulse',
   236→    'material.emissiveColor',
   237→    30,
   238→    Animation.ANIMATIONTYPE_COLOR3,
   239→    Animation.ANIMATIONLOOPMODE_CYCLE
   240→  );
   241→  rackPulse.setKeys([
   242→    { frame: 0, value: new Color3(0, 1, 0.25) },
   243→    { frame: 15, value: new Color3(0, 0.3, 0.1) },
   244→    { frame: 30, value: new Color3(0, 1, 0.25) },
   245→  ]);
   246→  rackLight.animations.push(rackPulse);
   247→  scene.beginAnimation(rackLight, 0, 30, true);
   248→
   249→  const equipmentRack = rackFrame; // Reference for interaction
   250→
   251→  // === SHOOTING RANGE (opposite side from equipment rack) ===
   252→  const shootingRangeContainer = new TransformNode('shootingRangeContainer', scene);
   253→  shootingRangeContainer.position.set(3.5, 0, -18);
   254→  shootingRangeContainer.parent = root;
   255→

   262→      depth: 0.8,
   263→    },
   264→    scene
   265→  );
   266→  rangeBooth.position.set(0, 0.6, 0);

   268→  rangeBooth.parent = shootingRangeContainer;
   269→  allMeshes.push(rangeBooth);
   270→
   271→  // Range screen (holographic display area)
   272→  const rangeScreen = MeshBuilder.CreatePlane(

   274→    {
   275→      width: 1.2,
   276→      height: 0.8,
   277→    },
   278→    scene
   279→  );

   284→
   285→  // Range indicator light
   286→  const rangeLight = MeshBuilder.CreateSphere(

   291→    scene
   292→  );

   296→  allMeshes.push(rangeLight);

   314→  // Target area (back wall behind player when at range)

   326→  targetBackdrop.parent = shootingRangeContainer;
   327→  allMeshes.push(targetBackdrop);
   328→
   329→  // Create holographic targets (initially invisible)
   330→  const targets: Mesh[] = [];
   331→  const targetMaterials: StandardMaterial[] = [];
   332→  const targetPositions = [
   333→    new Vector3(-0.8, 1.8, 2.8),
   334→    new Vector3(0.8, 1.2, 2.8),
   335→    new Vector3(0, 2.0, 2.8),
   336→    new Vector3(-0.5, 1.0, 2.8),
   337→    new Vector3(0.6, 1.6, 2.8),
   338→  ];
   339→
   340→  for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
   341→    // Outer ring
   342→    const targetRing = MeshBuilder.CreateTorus(
   343→      `targetRing_${i}`,
   344→      {
   345→        diameter: 0.4,
   346→        thickness: 0.03,
   347→        tessellation: 24,
   348→      },
   349→      scene
   350→    );
   351→    targetRing.position = targetPositions[i].clone();
   352→    targetRing.position.x += shootingRangeContainer.position.x;
   353→    targetRing.position.z += shootingRangeContainer.position.z;
   354→    targetRing.rotation.x = Math.PI / 2;
   355→
   356→    // Create new material for target ring (don't clone - can cause issues)
   357→    const targetMat = new StandardMaterial(`targetMat_${i}`, scene);
   358→    targetMat.emissiveColor = new Color3(1, 0.3, 0);
   359→    targetMat.diffuseColor = new Color3(0.3, 0.1, 0);
   360→    targetRing.material = targetMat;
   361→    targetRing.isVisible = false;
   362→    targetRing.parent = root;
   363→    allMeshes.push(targetRing);
   364→    targetMaterials.push(targetMat);
   365→
   366→    // Center point (hit detection)
   367→    const targetCenter = MeshBuilder.CreateDisc(
   368→      `targetCenter_${i}`,
   369→      {
   370→        radius: 0.12,
   371→        tessellation: 16,
   372→      },
   373→      scene
   374→    );
   375→    targetCenter.position = targetPositions[i].clone();
   376→    targetCenter.position.x += shootingRangeContainer.position.x;
   377→    targetCenter.position.z += shootingRangeContainer.position.z - 0.01;
   378→
   379→    // Create new material for center
   380→    const centerMat = new StandardMaterial(`centerMat_${i}`, scene);
   381→    centerMat.emissiveColor = new Color3(1, 0, 0);
   382→    centerMat.diffuseColor = new Color3(0.3, 0, 0);
   383→    targetCenter.material = centerMat;
   384→    targetCenter.isVisible = false;
   385→    targetCenter.parent = root;
   386→    allMeshes.push(targetCenter);
   387→    targetMaterials.push(centerMat);
   388→
   389→    targets.push(targetCenter);
   390→    targets.push(targetRing);
   391→  }
   392→
   393→  // Shooting range state
   394→  let calibrationActive = false;
   395→  let targetsHit: boolean[] = [false, false, false, false, false];
   396→  let rangeCallbacks: ShootingRangeCallbacks | null = null;
   397→
   398→  // === CEILING ===
   399→  const ceiling = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(
   400→    'ceiling',

   402→      width: corridorWidth,
   403→      height: 0.4,
   404→      depth: totalLength,
   405→    },
   406→    scene
   407→  );

   412→  allMeshes.push(ceiling);
   413→
   414→  // === OVERHEAD PIPES ===

   431→  }

   452→      width: 4,
   453→      height: corridorHeight - 0.5,
   454→      depth: 0.3,
   455→    },
   456→    scene
   457→  );
   458→  innerDoor.position.set(0, corridorHeight / 2, -prepBayLength);
   459→  innerDoor.material = materials.get('windowFrame')!;
   460→  innerDoor.parent = root;
   461→  allMeshes.push(innerDoor);
   462→
   463→  // Door status lights
   464→  const doorLightLeft = MeshBuilder.CreateSphere('doorLightL', { diameter: 0.2 }, scene);

   466→  doorLightLeft.material = materials.get('active')!;
   467→  doorLightLeft.parent = root;
   468→  allMeshes.push(doorLightLeft);
   469→
   470→  const doorLightRight = MeshBuilder.CreateSphere('doorLightR', { diameter: 0.2 }, scene);

   472→  doorLightRight.material = materials.get('active')!;
   473→  doorLightRight.parent = root;
   474→  allMeshes.push(doorLightRight);
   475→
   476→  // === HANGAR BAY SECTION ===
   477→  const hangarStart = -prepBayLength;
   478→
   479→  // Hangar walls - taller, industrial
   480→  for (let side = -1; side <= 1; side += 2) {
   481→    const hangarWall = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(

   600→  // Pod status lights

   606→    allMeshes.push(statusLight);
   607→  }
   608→
   609→  // === VIEWPORT (placeholder, will be replaced by open bay doors) ===
   610→  const viewport = MeshBuilder.CreateBox(

   623→
   624→  // === LIGHTING ===
   625→  // Prep bay lights
   626→  for (let z = 5; z < prepBayLength - 3; z += 8) {
   627→    const light = new PointLight(`prepLight_${z}`, new Vector3(0, corridorHeight - 0.5, -z), scene);
   628→    light.diffuse = new Color3(0.8, 0.9, 1.0);
   629→    light.intensity = 0.6;
   630→    light.range = 15;
   631→    lights.push(light);
   632→  }
   633→
   634→  // Hangar bay lights - more industrial orange
   635→  for (let z = prepBayLength + 5; z < totalLength - 5; z += 10) {
   636→    const light = new PointLight(`hangarLight_${z}`, new Vector3(0, corridorHeight + 1, -z), scene);
   637→    light.diffuse = new Color3(1.0, 0.8, 0.6);
   638→    light.intensity = 0.5;
   639→    light.range = 20;
   640→    lights.push(light);
   641→  }
   642→
   643→  // Emergency lights
   644→  for (let z = 0; z < totalLength; z += 15) {
   645→    const emergencyLight = MeshBuilder.CreateSphere('emergencyLight', { diameter: 0.2 }, scene);
   646→    emergencyLight.position.set(0, corridorHeight - 0.2, -z);
   647→    emergencyLight.material = materials.get('emergency')!;
   648→    emergencyLight.parent = root;
   649→    allMeshes.push(emergencyLight);
   650→
   651→    const pulseAnim = new Animation(
   652→      'pulse',
   653→      'material.emissiveColor',
   654→      30,
   655→      Animation.ANIMATIONTYPE_COLOR3,
   656→      Animation.ANIMATIONLOOPMODE_CYCLE
   657→    );
   658→    pulseAnim.setKeys([
   659→      { frame: 0, value: new Color3(1, 0, 0) },
   660→      { frame: 15, value: new Color3(0.3, 0, 0) },
   661→      { frame: 30, value: new Color3(1, 0, 0) },
   662→    ]);
   663→    emergencyLight.animations.push(pulseAnim);
   664→    scene.beginAnimation(emergencyLight, 0, 30, true);
   665→  }
   666→
   667→  // === ANIMATION FUNCTIONS ===
   668→
   669→  // Equip suit animation - suit disappears, HUD flash
   670→  const playEquipSuit = (callback: () => void) => {
   671→    // Fade out suit
   672→    const fadeAnim = new Animation(
   673→      'fadeOut',
   674→      'visibility',
   675→      30,
   676→      Animation.ANIMATIONTYPE_FLOAT,
   677→      Animation.ANIMATIONLOOPMODE_CONSTANT
   678→    );
   679→    fadeAnim.setKeys([
   680→      { frame: 0, value: 1 },
   681→      { frame: 30, value: 0 },
   682→    ]);
   683→    suitBody.animations = [fadeAnim];
   684→    suitHelmet.animations = [fadeAnim];
   685→
   686→    scene.beginAnimation(suitBody, 0, 30, false);
   687→    scene.beginAnimation(suitHelmet, 0, 30, false, 1, () => {
   688→      // Stop rack light pulsing, turn solid
   689→      scene.stopAnimation(rackLight);
   690→      (rackLight.material as StandardMaterial).emissiveColor = new Color3(0.2, 0.2, 0.2);
   691→      callback();
   692→    });
   693→  };
   694→
   695→  // Depressurize - change door lights to red, play alarm effect
   696→  const playDepressurize = (callback: () => void) => {
   697→    // Change door lights to red (cycling)
   698→    const redPulse = new Animation(
   699→      'redPulse',
   700→      'material.emissiveColor',
   701→      30,
   702→      Animation.ANIMATIONTYPE_COLOR3,
   703→      Animation.ANIMATIONLOOPMODE_CYCLE
   704→    );
   705→    redPulse.setKeys([
   706→      { frame: 0, value: new Color3(1, 0, 0) },
   707→      { frame: 15, value: new Color3(0.3, 0, 0) },
   708→      { frame: 30, value: new Color3(1, 0, 0) },
   709→    ]);
   710→    doorLightLeft.animations = [redPulse];
   711→    doorLightRight.animations = [redPulse];
   712→    scene.beginAnimation(doorLightLeft, 0, 30, true);
   713→    scene.beginAnimation(doorLightRight, 0, 30, true);
   714→
   715→    setTimeout(callback, 3000);
   716→  };
   717→
   718→  // Open bay doors - dramatic sliding animation
   719→  const playOpenBayDoors = (callback: () => void) => {
   720→    const doorOpenLeft = new Animation(
   721→      'doorOpenL',
   722→      'position.x',
   723→      30,
   724→      Animation.ANIMATIONTYPE_FLOAT,
   725→      Animation.ANIMATIONLOOPMODE_CONSTANT
   726→    );
   727→    doorOpenLeft.setKeys([
   728→      { frame: 0, value: bayDoorLeft.position.x },
   729→      { frame: 90, value: bayDoorLeft.position.x - bayDoorWidth - 1 },
   730→    ]);
   731→
   732→    const doorOpenRight = new Animation(
   733→      'doorOpenR',
   734→      'position.x',
   735→      30,
   736→      Animation.ANIMATIONTYPE_FLOAT,
   737→      Animation.ANIMATIONLOOPMODE_CONSTANT
   738→    );
   739→    doorOpenRight.setKeys([
   740→      { frame: 0, value: bayDoorRight.position.x },
   741→      { frame: 90, value: bayDoorRight.position.x + bayDoorWidth + 1 },
   742→    ]);
   743→
   744→    bayDoorLeft.animations = [doorOpenLeft];
   745→    bayDoorRight.animations = [doorOpenRight];
   746→
   747→    scene.beginAnimation(bayDoorLeft, 0, 90, false);
   748→    scene.beginAnimation(bayDoorRight, 0, 90, false, 1, callback);
   749→  };
   750→
   751→  // Enter pod - pod door close effect
   752→  const playEnterPod = (callback: () => void) => {
   753→    // Flash pod lights
   754→    setTimeout(callback, 1500);
   755→  };
   756→
   757→  // Launch - pod drops away
   758→  const playLaunch = (callback: () => void) => {
   759→    const podDrop = new Animation(
   760→      'podDrop',
   761→      'position.y',
   762→      30,
   763→      Animation.ANIMATIONTYPE_FLOAT,
   764→      Animation.ANIMATIONLOOPMODE_CONSTANT
   765→    );
   766→    podDrop.setKeys([
   767→      { frame: 0, value: dropPod.position.y },
   768→      { frame: 10, value: dropPod.position.y - 0.5 },
   769→      { frame: 60, value: dropPod.position.y - 50 },
   770→    ]);
   771→
   772→    const coneDrop = new Animation(
   773→      'coneDrop',
   774→      'position.y',
   775→      30,
   776→      Animation.ANIMATIONTYPE_FLOAT,
   777→      Animation.ANIMATIONLOOPMODE_CONSTANT
   778→    );
   779→    coneDrop.setKeys([
   780→      { frame: 0, value: podCone.position.y },
   781→      { frame: 10, value: podCone.position.y - 0.5 },
   782→      { frame: 60, value: podCone.position.y - 50 },
   783→    ]);
   784→
   785→    dropPod.animations = [podDrop];
   786→    podCone.animations = [coneDrop];
   787→
   788→    scene.beginAnimation(dropPod, 0, 60, false);
   789→    scene.beginAnimation(podCone, 0, 60, false, 1, callback);
   790→  };
   791→
   792→  // Start calibration mini-game
   793→  const startCalibration = (callbacks: ShootingRangeCallbacks) => {
   794→    calibrationActive = true;
   795→    rangeCallbacks = callbacks;
   796→    targetsHit = [false, false, false, false, false];
   797→
   798→    // Stop range light pulsing, make it amber (active range)
   799→    scene.stopAnimation(rangeLight);
   800→    (rangeLight.material as StandardMaterial).emissiveColor = new Color3(1, 0.6, 0);
   801→
   802→    // Show all targets with staggered animation
   803→    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
   804→      const ringIndex = i * 2 + 1;
   805→      const centerIndex = i * 2;
   806→
   807→      setTimeout(() => {
   808→        if (targets[ringIndex]) targets[ringIndex].isVisible = true;
   809→        if (targets[centerIndex]) targets[centerIndex].isVisible = true;
   810→
   811→        // Pulse animation on appearance
   812→        const targetMat = targets[ringIndex].material as StandardMaterial;
   813→        const originalColor = targetMat.emissiveColor.clone();
   814→        targetMat.emissiveColor = new Color3(1, 1, 1);
   815→        setTimeout(() => {
   816→          targetMat.emissiveColor = originalColor;
   817→        }, 100);
   818→      }, i * 200);
   819→    }
   820→  };
   821→
   822→  // Check if ray hits a target
   823→  const checkTargetHit = (rayOrigin: Vector3, rayDirection: Vector3): boolean => {
   824→    if (!calibrationActive) return false;
   825→
   826→    // Simple ray-sphere intersection for each unhit target
   827→    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
   828→      if (targetsHit[i]) continue;
   829→
   830→      const centerIndex = i * 2;
   831→      const ringIndex = i * 2 + 1;
   832→      const targetCenter = targets[centerIndex];
   833→      if (!targetCenter) continue;
   834→
   835→      // Get target world position
   836→      const targetPos = targetCenter.getAbsolutePosition();
   837→
   838→      // Ray-sphere intersection (generous hit radius)
   839→      const hitRadius = 0.25;
   840→      const toTarget = targetPos.subtract(rayOrigin);
   841→      const projection = Vector3.Dot(toTarget, rayDirection);
   842→
   843→      if (projection < 0) continue; // Target behind ray
   844→
   845→      const closestPoint = rayOrigin.add(rayDirection.scale(projection));
   846→      const distance = Vector3.Distance(closestPoint, targetPos);
   847→
   848→      if (distance <= hitRadius) {
   849→        // Hit!
   850→        targetsHit[i] = true;
   851→
   852→        // Visual feedback - flash green then hide
   853→        const ringMat = targets[ringIndex].material as StandardMaterial;
   854→        const centerMat = targetCenter.material as StandardMaterial;
   855→
   856→        ringMat.emissiveColor = new Color3(0, 1, 0.3);
   857→        centerMat.emissiveColor = new Color3(0, 1, 0.3);
   858→
   859→        setTimeout(() => {
   860→          targets[ringIndex].isVisible = false;
   861→          targetCenter.isVisible = false;
   862→        }, 150);
   863→
   864→        rangeCallbacks?.onTargetHit(i);
   865→
   866→        // Check if all targets hit
   867→        if (targetsHit.every((hit) => hit)) {
   868→          calibrationActive = false;
   869→          // Range light back to green
   870→          (rangeLight.material as StandardMaterial).emissiveColor = new Color3(0, 1, 0.25);
   871→          rangeCallbacks?.onAllTargetsHit();
   872→        }
   873→
   874→        return true;
   875→      }
   876→    }
   877→
   878→    return false;
   879→  };
   880→
   881→  const isCalibrationActive = () => calibrationActive;
   882→
   883→  // Dispose function
   884→  const dispose = () => {
   885→    for (const mesh of allMeshes) {
   886→      mesh.dispose();
   887→    }
   888→    for (const light of lights) {
   889→      light.dispose();
   890→    }
   891→    for (const mat of targetMaterials) {
   892→      mat.dispose();
   893→    }
   894→    disposeMaterials(materials);
   895→    root.dispose();
   896→  };
   897→
   898→  return {
   899→    root,
   900→    dropPod,
   901→    viewport,
   902→    equipmentRack,
   903→    shootingRange: shootingRangeContainer,
   904→    innerDoor,
   905→    bayDoorLeft,
   906→    bayDoorRight,
   907→    lights,
   908→    playEquipSuit,
   909→    playDepressurize,
   910→    playOpenBayDoors,
   911→    playEnterPod,
   912→    playLaunch,
   913→    startCalibration,
   914→    checkTargetHit,
   915→    isCalibrationActive,
   916→    dispose,
   917→  };
   918→}
   919→

// Main Audio Manager class
export class AudioManager {
  private scene: Scene | null = null;
  private sounds: Map<string, Sound> = new Map();
  private proceduralAudio: ProceduralAudio;

  private masterVolume = 1.0;
  private sfxVolume = 0.7;
  private musicVolume = 0.5;

  private isMuted = false;
  private currentMusic: Sound | null = null;
  private activeLoops: Map<string, { stop: () => void }> = new Map();

  // HTML5 Audio for music playback
  private musicAudio: HTMLAudioElement | null = null;
  private currentMusicTrack: MusicTrack | null = null;
  private musicFadeInterval: number | null = null;

  constructor() {
    this.proceduralAudio = new ProceduralAudio();
  }

  initialize(scene: Scene): void {
    this.scene = scene;
  }

  // Play a music track with optional crossfade
  playMusic(track: MusicTrack, crossfadeDuration = 1000): void {
    if (this.isMuted) return;
    if (this.currentMusicTrack === track && this.musicAudio && !this.musicAudio.paused) {
      return; // Already playing this track
    }

    const targetVolume = this.musicVolume * this.masterVolume;

    // If there's existing music, fade it out
    if (this.musicAudio && !this.musicAudio.paused) {
      this.fadeOutMusic(crossfadeDuration, () => {
        this.startNewTrack(track, targetVolume, crossfadeDuration);
      });
    } else {
      this.startNewTrack(track, targetVolume, crossfadeDuration);
    }
  }

  private startNewTrack(track: MusicTrack, targetVolume: number, fadeDuration: number): void {
    const path = MUSIC_PATHS[track];
    if (!path) {
      console.warn(`No music path for track: ${track}`);
      return;
    }

    // Create new audio element
    this.musicAudio = new Audio(path);
    this.musicAudio.loop = true;
    this.musicAudio.volume = 0;
    this.currentMusicTrack = track;

    // Start playing and fade in
    this.musicAudio.play().then(() => {
      this.fadeInMusic(targetVolume, fadeDuration);
    }).catch((e) => {
      console.warn('Music playback failed (user interaction may be required):', e);
    });
  }

  private fadeInMusic(targetVolume: number, duration: number): void {
    if (!this.musicAudio) return;

    if (this.musicFadeInterval) {
      clearInterval(this.musicFadeInterval);
    }

    const steps = 20;
    const stepTime = duration / steps;
    const volumeStep = targetVolume / steps;
    let currentStep = 0;

    this.musicFadeInterval = window.setInterval(() => {
      currentStep++;
      if (this.musicAudio) {
        this.musicAudio.volume = Math.min(targetVolume, volumeStep * currentStep);
      }
      if (currentStep >= steps) {
        if (this.musicFadeInterval) clearInterval(this.musicFadeInterval);
        this.musicFadeInterval = null;
      }
    }, stepTime);
  }

  private fadeOutMusic(duration: number, onComplete?: () => void): void {
    if (!this.musicAudio) {
      onComplete?.();
      return;
    }

    if (this.musicFadeInterval) {
      clearInterval(this.musicFadeInterval);
    }

    const startVolume = this.musicAudio.volume;
    const steps = 20;
    const stepTime = duration / steps;
    const volumeStep = startVolume / steps;
    let currentStep = 0;
    const audioToFade = this.musicAudio;

    this.musicFadeInterval = window.setInterval(() => {
      currentStep++;
      audioToFade.volume = Math.max(0, startVolume - volumeStep * currentStep);

      if (currentStep >= steps) {
        if (this.musicFadeInterval) clearInterval(this.musicFadeInterval);
        this.musicFadeInterval = null;
        audioToFade.pause();
        audioToFade.src = '';
        onComplete?.();
      }
    }, stepTime);
  }

  stopMusic(fadeDuration = 1000): void {
    this.fadeOutMusic(fadeDuration, () => {
      this.musicAudio = null;
      this.currentMusicTrack = null;
    });
  }

  getCurrentMusicTrack(): MusicTrack | null {
    return this.currentMusicTrack;
  }
