/**
 * Assemblages - Pre-configured entity groups for procedural scene generation
 *
 * Design principles:
 * 1. Each assemblage is a self-contained chunk that can be spawned/despawned
 * 2. Assemblages snap to a 4-unit grid (matching PSX Mega Pack modular system)
 * 3. Assemblages are serializable to SQLite for persistence
 * 4. Visited locations are persisted so they don't change on revisit
 */

import type { Vector3 } from '@babylonjs/core/Maths/math.vector';
import type { StructuralEntity } from '../components/structural';

export const CHUNK_SIZE = 32; // 32 units = 8 grid tiles (4 units each)
export const RENDER_RADIUS = 3; // Chunks around player to render
export const UNLOAD_RADIUS = 5; // Chunks to keep in memory before unloading

// ============================================================================
// ASSEMBLAGE TYPES
// ============================================================================

export type EnvironmentType =
  | 'station_interior'   // Anchor Station
  | 'surface_rocky'      // Proxima surface
  | 'fob_military'       // FOB Delta
  | 'hive_organic'       // Chitin hive tunnels
  | 'canyon'             // Canyon terrain
  | 'extraction_zone';   // LZ Omega

export type AssemblageType =
  // Station Interior
  | 'corridor_straight' | 'corridor_corner' | 'corridor_t' | 'corridor_cross'
  | 'room_small' | 'room_medium' | 'room_large'
  | 'hangar_bay' | 'airlock'
  | 'quarters' | 'command_deck' | 'engineering'
  // Surface Rocky
  | 'terrain_flat' | 'terrain_rocky' | 'terrain_crater'
  | 'rock_cluster' | 'boulder_field'
  | 'alien_vegetation'
  // FOB Military
  | 'prefab_barracks' | 'prefab_command' | 'prefab_vehicle_bay'
  | 'perimeter_wall' | 'perimeter_gate'
  | 'comms_tower' | 'power_generator'
  // Hive Organic
  | 'tunnel_straight' | 'tunnel_branch' | 'tunnel_chamber'
  | 'egg_chamber' | 'queen_chamber'
  | 'hive_entrance'
  // Common
  | 'spawn_point' | 'objective_marker' | 'loot_cache';

// ============================================================================
// ASSEMBLAGE DEFINITION
// ============================================================================

export interface AssemblageConnection {
  direction: 'north' | 'south' | 'east' | 'west' | 'up' | 'down';
  type: 'door' | 'open' | 'wall' | 'sealed';
  offset: { x: number; z: number }; // offset from chunk center in grid units
}

export interface AssemblageDefinition {
  type: AssemblageType;
  environment: EnvironmentType;

  // Size in grid units (4-unit grid)
  gridWidth: number;
  gridDepth: number;
  gridHeight: number;

  // Connection points for procedural linking
  connections: AssemblageConnection[];

  // Entities that make up this assemblage
  entities: AssemblageEntityDef[];

  // Spawn configuration
  enemySpawns?: { maxCount: number; types: string[]; waveDelay?: number }[];
  lootSpawns?: { position: { x: number; y: number; z: number }; lootTable: string }[];

  // Navigation
  navmeshIncluded: boolean;
  coverPoints: { x: number; y: number; z: number; direction: { x: number; z: number } }[];

  // Tags for filtering
  tags: string[];
}

export interface AssemblageEntityDef {
  type: 'structural' | 'prop' | 'light' | 'door' | 'trigger' | 'spawn';
  modelPath?: string;
  position: { x: number; y: number; z: number };
  rotation?: { x: number; y: number; z: number };
  scale?: number;
  components: Partial<StructuralEntity>;
}

// ============================================================================
// CHUNK STATE FOR PERSISTENCE
// ============================================================================

export interface ChunkState {
  chunkX: number;
  chunkZ: number;
  environment: EnvironmentType;

  // Generation seed for reproducibility
  seed: number;

  // Which assemblages were placed
  assemblages: PlacedAssemblage[];

  // Dynamic state that persists
  doors: { entityId: string; state: string }[];
  loot: { entityId: string; collected: boolean }[];
  enemies: { entityId: string; dead: boolean; position?: { x: number; y: number; z: number } }[];
  triggers: { entityId: string; triggered: boolean }[];

  // Meta
  firstVisited: number; // timestamp
  lastVisited: number;
  fullyExplored: boolean;
}

export interface PlacedAssemblage {
  type: AssemblageType;
  gridX: number; // Position within chunk
  gridZ: number;
  rotation: 0 | 90 | 180 | 270;
  entityIds: string[]; // IDs of spawned entities
}

// ============================================================================
// STATION INTERIOR ASSEMBLAGES
// ============================================================================

export const STATION_ASSEMBLAGES: Record<string, AssemblageDefinition> = {
  corridor_straight: {
    type: 'corridor_straight',

📝 Write ChunkManager.ts

/**
 * ChunkManager - Handles procedural loading/unloading of world chunks
 *
 * Key features:
 * 1. Loads chunks in a radius around the player
 * 2. Unloads chunks beyond the render radius to save memory
 * 3. Persists chunk state to SQLite so visited locations don't change
 * 4. Uses deterministic seeding for reproducible generation
 */

import type { Vector3 } from '@babylonjs/core/Maths/math.vector';
import type { Scene } from '@babylonjs/core/scene';
import { TransformNode } from '@babylonjs/core/Meshes/transformNode';
import { worldDb } from '../db/worldDatabase';
import {
  type AssemblageDefinition,
  type ChunkState,
  type EnvironmentType,
  type PlacedAssemblage,
  CHUNK_SIZE,
  RENDER_RADIUS,
  UNLOAD_RADIUS,
  getAssemblagesByEnvironment,
  ALL_ASSEMBLAGES,
} from './assemblages';
import { world, createEntity, removeEntity, type Entity } from '../core/ecs';

// Seeded random number generator for reproducible chunk generation
class SeededRandom {
  private seed: number;

  constructor(seed: number) {
    this.seed = seed;
  }

  // Mulberry32 PRNG
  next(): number {
    let t = (this.seed += 0x6d2b79f5);
    t = Math.imul(t ^ (t >>> 15), t | 1);
    t ^= t + Math.imul(t ^ (t >>> 7), t | 61);
    return ((t ^ (t >>> 14)) >>> 0) / 4294967296;
  }

  nextInt(min: number, max: number): number {
    return Math.floor(this.next() * (max - min + 1)) + min;
  }

  pick<T>(array: T[]): T {
    return array[Math.floor(this.next() * array.length)];
  }

  shuffle<T>(array: T[]): T[] {
    const result = [...array];
    for (let i = result.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
      const j = Math.floor(this.next() * (i + 1));
      [result[i], result[j]] = [result[j], result[i]];
    }
    return result;
  }
}

// Hash function for generating chunk seeds
function hashChunkCoords(x: number, z: number, worldSeed: number): number {
  // Simple but effective hash combining coordinates with world seed
  let hash = worldSeed;
  hash = ((hash << 5) - hash + x) | 0;
  hash = ((hash << 5) - hash + z) | 0;
  hash = ((hash << 5) - hash + x * z) | 0;
  return Math.abs(hash);
}

interface LoadedChunk {
  x: number;
  z: number;
  state: ChunkState;
  root: TransformNode;
  entities: Entity[];
  lastAccessed: number;
}

export class ChunkManager {
  private scene: Scene;
  private worldSeed: number;
  private environment: EnvironmentType;
  private loadedChunks: Map<string, LoadedChunk> = new Map();
  private loadingChunks: Set<string> = new Set();
  private playerChunkX = 0;
  private playerChunkZ = 0;
  private root: TransformNode;

  constructor(scene: Scene, worldSeed: number, environment: EnvironmentType) {
    this.scene = scene;
    this.worldSeed = worldSeed;
    this.environment = environment;
    this.root = new TransformNode('chunkManager', scene);
  }

  private getChunkKey(x: number, z: number): string {
    return `${x},${z}`;
  }

  private worldToChunk(worldPos: Vector3): { x: number; z: number } {
    return {
      x: Math.floor(worldPos.x / CHUNK_SIZE),
      z: Math.floor(worldPos.z / CHUNK_SIZE),
    };
  }

  /**
   * Update chunk loading based on player position
   */
  async update(playerPosition: Vector3): Promise<void> {
    const playerChunk = this.worldToChunk(playerPosition);

    // Check if player has moved to a new chunk
    if (playerChunk.x !== this.playerChunkX || playerChunk.z !== this.playerChunkZ) {
      this.playerChunkX = playerChunk.x;
      this.playerChunkZ = playerChunk.z;

      // Trigger chunk loading/unloading
      await this.updateLoadedChunks();
    }

    // Update last accessed time for chunks player is near
    const nearbyKey = this.getChunkKey(playerChunk.x, playerChunk.z);
    const nearbyChunk = this.loadedChunks.get(nearbyKey);
    if (nearbyChunk) {
      nearbyChunk.lastAccessed = Date.now();
    }
  }

  /**
   * Load chunks in render radius, unload those outside
   */
  private async updateLoadedChunks(): Promise<void> {
    const chunksToLoad: { x: number; z: number }[] = [];
    const chunksToUnload: string[] = [];

    // Determine which chunks should be loaded
    for (let dx = -RENDER_RADIUS; dx <= RENDER_RADIUS; dx++) {
      for (let dz = -RENDER_RADIUS; dz <= RENDER_RADIUS; dz++) {
        const x = this.playerChunkX + dx;
        const z = this.playerChunkZ + dz;
        const key = this.getChunkKey(x, z);

        if (!this.loadedChunks.has(key) && !this.loadingChunks.has(key)) {
          chunksToLoad.push({ x, z });
        }
      }
    }

    // Determine which chunks should be unloaded
    for (const [key, chunk] of this.loadedChunks) {
      const dx = Math.abs(chunk.x - this.playerChunkX);
      const dz = Math.abs(chunk.z - this.playerChunkZ);

      if (dx > UNLOAD_RADIUS || dz > UNLOAD_RADIUS) {
        chunksToUnload.push(key);
      }
    }

    // Unload distant chunks first (frees memory)
    for (const key of chunksToUnload) {
      await this.unloadChunk(key);
    }

    // Load new chunks (prioritize closer ones)
    chunksToLoad.sort((a, b) => {
      const distA = Math.abs(a.x - this.playerChunkX) + Math.abs(a.z - this.playerChunkZ);
      const distB = Math.abs(b.x - this.playerChunkX) + Math.abs(b.z - this.playerChunkZ);
      return distA - distB;
    });

    // Load chunks in batches to avoid frame drops
    const BATCH_SIZE = 2;
    for (let i = 0; i < Math.min(chunksToLoad.length, BATCH_SIZE); i++) {
      const { x, z } = chunksToLoad[i];
      await this.loadChunk(x, z);
    }
  }

  /**
   * Load a chunk - either from database or generate new
   */
  private async loadChunk(x: number, z: number): Promise<void> {
    const key = this.getChunkKey(x, z);
    if (this.loadedChunks.has(key) || this.loadingChunks.has(key)) {
      return;
    }

    this.loadingChunks.add(key);

    try {
      // Check if chunk exists in database
      let state = await this.loadChunkState(x, z);

      if (!state) {
        // Generate new chunk
        state = await this.generateChunk(x, z);
        // Save to database
        await this.saveChunkState(state);
      }

      // Spawn the chunk in the scene
      const loaded = await this.spawnChunk(state);
      this.loadedChunks.set(key, loaded);

    } catch (error) {
      console.error(`Failed to load chunk ${key}:`, error);
    } finally {
      this.loadingChunks.delete(key);
    }
  }

  /**
   * Unload a chunk - save state and remove from scene
   */
  private async unloadChunk(key: string): Promise<void> {
    const chunk = this.loadedChunks.get(key);
    if (!chunk) return;

    // Update state with current entity states
    await this.updateChunkState(chunk);

    // Save to database
    await this.saveChunkState(chunk.state);

    // Remove entities from ECS
    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
      removeEntity(entity);
    }

    // Dispose scene objects
    chunk.root.dispose();

    this.loadedChunks.delete(key);
  }

  /**
   * Generate a new chunk using seeded random and assemblages
   */
  private async generateChunk(x: number, z: number): Promise<ChunkState> {
    const seed = hashChunkCoords(x, z, this.worldSeed);
    const rng = new SeededRandom(seed);

    const state: ChunkState = {
      chunkX: x,
      chunkZ: z,
      environment: this.environment,
      seed,
      assemblages: [],
      doors: [],
      loot: [],
      enemies: [],
      triggers: [],
      firstVisited: Date.now(),
      lastVisited: Date.now(),
      fullyExplored: false,
    };

    // Get available assemblages for this environment
    const available = getAssemblagesByEnvironment(this.environment);

    if (available.length === 0) {
      console.warn(`No assemblages for environment: ${this.environment}`);
      return state;
    }

    // Simple generation: place assemblages based on environment type
    if (this.environment === 'station_interior') {
      // Interior: corridor-based layout
      this.generateInteriorLayout(state, rng, available);
    } else if (this.environment === 'surface_rocky') {
      // Exterior: terrain with scattered features
      this.generateExteriorLayout(state, rng, available);
    } else if (this.environment === 'hive_organic') {
      // Hive: tunnel network
      this.generateHiveLayout(state, rng, available);
    }

    return state;
  }

  private generateInteriorLayout(
    state: ChunkState,
    rng: SeededRandom,
    available: AssemblageDefinition[]
  ): void {
    // For interior, create a corridor network
    const corridors = available.filter(a =>
      a.type.startsWith('corridor') || a.type === 'airlock'
    );

    if (corridors.length === 0) return;

    // Place 2-4 assemblages per chunk
    const count = rng.nextInt(2, 4);
    const gridSize = CHUNK_SIZE / 4; // 8 grid cells per chunk

    for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
      const assemblage = rng.pick(corridors);
      const gridX = rng.nextInt(0, gridSize - assemblage.gridWidth);
      const gridZ = rng.nextInt(0, gridSize - assemblage.gridDepth);
      const rotation = rng.pick([0, 90, 180, 270]) as 0 | 90 | 180 | 270;

      state.assemblages.push({
        type: assemblage.type,
        gridX,
        gridZ,
        rotation,
        entityIds: [], // Will be filled when spawned
      });
    }
  }

  private generateExteriorLayout(
    state: ChunkState,
    rng: SeededRandom,
    available: AssemblageDefinition[]
  ): void {
    // Always have base terrain
    const terrains = available.filter(a => a.type.startsWith('terrain'));
    if (terrains.length > 0) {
      state.assemblages.push({
        type: 'terrain_flat',
        gridX: 0,
        gridZ: 0,
        rotation: 0,
        entityIds: [],
      });
    }

    // Add rock clusters randomly
    const rocks = available.filter(a => a.type === 'rock_cluster');
    if (rocks.length > 0) {
      const rockCount = rng.nextInt(0, 5);
      for (let i = 0; i < rockCount; i++) {
        const gridX = rng.nextInt(0, 6);
        const gridZ = rng.nextInt(0, 6);

        state.assemblages.push({
          type: 'rock_cluster',
          gridX,
          gridZ,
          rotation: rng.pick([0, 90, 180, 270]) as 0 | 90 | 180 | 270,
          entityIds: [],
        });
      }
    }
  }

  private generateHiveLayout(
    state: ChunkState,
    rng: SeededRandom,
    available: AssemblageDefinition[]
  ): void {
    const tunnels = available.filter(a =>
      a.type.startsWith('tunnel') || a.type === 'egg_chamber'
    );

    if (tunnels.length === 0) return;

    // Hives are more connected - create a branching network
    const count = rng.nextInt(1, 3);
    const gridSize = CHUNK_SIZE / 4;

    for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
      const assemblage = rng.pick(tunnels);
      const gridX = rng.nextInt(0, gridSize - assemblage.gridWidth);
      const gridZ = rng.nextInt(0, gridSize - assemblage.gridDepth);

      state.assemblages.push({
        type: assemblage.type,
        gridX,
        gridZ,
        rotation: rng.pick([0, 90, 180, 270]) as 0 | 90 | 180 | 270,
        entityIds: [],
      });
    }
  }

  /**
   * Spawn chunk entities in the scene
   */
  private async spawnChunk(state: ChunkState): Promise<LoadedChunk> {
    const chunkRoot = new TransformNode(
      `chunk_${state.chunkX}_${state.chunkZ}`,
      this.scene
    );
    chunkRoot.parent = this.root;

    // Position chunk in world space
    chunkRoot.position.x = state.chunkX * CHUNK_SIZE;
    chunkRoot.position.z = state.chunkZ * CHUNK_SIZE;

    const entities: Entity[] = [];

    // Spawn each assemblage
    for (const placed of state.assemblages) {
      const def = ALL_ASSEMBLAGES[placed.type];
      if (!def) {
        console.warn(`Unknown assemblage type: ${placed.type}`);
        continue;
      }

      // Create assemblage root
      const assembRoot = new TransformNode(
        `assem_${placed.type}_${placed.gridX}_${placed.gridZ}`,
        this.scene
      );
      assembRoot.parent = chunkRoot;
      assembRoot.position.x = placed.gridX * 4;
      assembRoot.position.z = placed.gridZ * 4;
      assembRoot.rotation.y = (placed.rotation * Math.PI) / 180;

      // Spawn entities from assemblage definition
      for (const entDef of def.entities) {
        const entity = createEntity({
          ...entDef.components,
          tags: {
            ...entDef.components.tags,
            structural: entDef.type === 'structural',
          },
        });

        placed.entityIds.push(entity.id);
        entities.push(entity);

        // TODO: Load actual mesh from modelPath
        // For now, just create placeholder
      }
    }

    return {
      x: state.chunkX,
      z: state.chunkZ,
      state,
      root: chunkRoot,
      entities,
      lastAccessed: Date.now(),
    };
  }

  /**
   * Update chunk state from current entity states (for persistence)
   */
  private async updateChunkState(chunk: LoadedChunk): Promise<void> {
    chunk.state.lastVisited = Date.now();

    // Update door states
    chunk.state.doors = [];
    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
      if (entity.door) {
        chunk.state.doors.push({
          entityId: entity.id,
          state: entity.door.state,
        });
      }
    }

    // Update enemy states
    chunk.state.enemies = [];
    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
      if (entity.tags?.enemy && entity.health) {
        chunk.state.enemies.push({
          entityId: entity.id,
          dead: entity.health.current <= 0,
          position: entity.transform ? {
            x: entity.transform.position.x,
            y: entity.transform.position.y,
            z: entity.transform.position.z,
          } : undefined,
        });
      }
    }

    // Update loot states
    chunk.state.loot = [];
    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
      if (entity.prop?.contents) {
        chunk.state.loot.push({
          entityId: entity.id,
          collected: entity.prop.used,
        });
      }
    }

    // Update trigger states
    chunk.state.triggers = [];
    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
      if (entity.triggerZone) {
        chunk.state.triggers.push({
          entityId: entity.id,
          triggered: entity.triggerZone.triggered,
        });
      }
    }
  }

  /**
   * Load chunk state from SQLite
   */
  private async loadChunkState(x: number, z: number): Promise<ChunkState | null> {
    try {
      const key = `chunk_${this.environment}_${x}_${z}`;
      const data = worldDb.getChunkData(key);
      if (data) {
        return JSON.parse(data) as ChunkState;
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.warn(`Failed to load chunk state: ${error}`);
    }
    return null;
  }

  /**
   * Save chunk state to SQLite
   */
  private async saveChunkState(state: ChunkState): Promise<void> {
    try {
      const key = `chunk_${this.environment}_${state.chunkX}_${state.chunkZ}`;
      const data = JSON.stringify(state);
      worldDb.setChunkData(key, data);
    } catch (error) {
      console.warn(`Failed to save chunk state: ${error}`);
    }
  }

  /**
   * Force reload all chunks (e.g., after environment change)
   */
  async reloadAll(): Promise<void> {
    // Unload all current chunks
    for (const key of [...this.loadedChunks.keys()]) {
      await this.unloadChunk(key);
    }

    // Reload around player
    await this.updateLoadedChunks();
  }

  /**
   * Change environment type (e.g., entering hive from surface)
   */
  async setEnvironment(env: EnvironmentType): Promise<void> {
    if (env === this.environment) return;

    this.environment = env;
    await this.reloadAll();
  }

  /**
   * Get currently loaded chunk count
   */
  getLoadedChunkCount(): number {
    return this.loadedChunks.size;
  }

  /**
   * Dispose all resources
   */
  dispose(): void {
    for (const chunk of this.loadedChunks.values()) {
      for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
        removeEntity(entity);
      }
      chunk.root.dispose();
    }
    this.loadedChunks.clear();
    this.root.dispose();
  }
}

I need to add getChunkData and setChunkData methods that work with the ChunkManager. Looking at the ChunkManager.ts code referenced in the summary, it expects:
- worldDb.getChunkData(key) - returns ChunkState | null
- worldDb.setChunkData(key, data) - saves ChunkState


The ChunkState interface from assemblages/index.ts has:


export interface ChunkState {
  chunkX: number;
  chunkZ: number;
  environment: 'station_interior' | 'surface_rocky' | 'hive_organic';
  seed: number;
  entities: Array<{
    id: string;
    assemblage: string;
    position: [number, number, number];
    rotation: number;
    customData?: Record<string, unknown>;
  }>;
  generated: boolean;
  visited: boolean;
  lastVisited: number;
}



The current database already has a chunks table with columns:
- chunk_x, chunk_z, seed, buildings, obstacles, enemies, visited, created_at


But the ChunkState interface is more comprehensive. I need to either:
1. Create new methods that work with a JSON blob for the whole ChunkState
2. Modify the table schema


Since we want the ChunkManager to use its own data format, I'll add new methods that use a different approach - storing the full ChunkState as JSON in a new column or using the existing fields but mapping them appropriately.


Looking at the existing ChunkData interface vs ChunkState:
- ChunkData: chunkX, chunkZ, seed, buildings (JSON), obstacles (JSON), enemies (JSON), visited
- ChunkState: chunkX, chunkZ, environment, seed, entities (array), generated, visited, lastVisited


These are different structures. The existing saveChunk/getChunk methods work with ChunkData, while the ChunkManager needs ChunkState.


I'll create a separate chunk_state table to store the full ChunkState as JSON, maintaining backward compatibility with the existing chunks table. The ChunkManager uses a string key format of ${chunkX},${chunkZ}, so I'll implement getChunkState and setChunkState methods that parse this key and query the new table accordingly.


For the schema, I'll use a table with chunk_x and chunk_z as a composite primary key, plus a state column for the serialized ChunkState object. This allows efficient lookups and updates by chunk coordinates. I should also check what the ChunkManager interface actually requires to ensure compatibility.

     1→/**
     2→ * ChunkManager - Handles procedural loading/unloading of world chunks
     3→ *
     4→ * Key features:
     5→ * 1. Loads chunks in a radius around the player
     6→ * 2. Unloads chunks beyond the render radius to save memory
     7→ * 3. Persists chunk state to SQLite so visited locations don't change
     8→ * 4. Uses deterministic seeding for reproducible generation
     9→ */
    10→
    11→import type { Vector3 } from '@babylonjs/core/Maths/math.vector';
    12→import type { Scene } from '@babylonjs/core/scene';
    13→import { TransformNode } from '@babylonjs/core/Meshes/transformNode';
    14→import { worldDb } from '../db/worldDatabase';
    15→import {
    16→  type AssemblageDefinition,
    17→  type ChunkState,
    18→  type EnvironmentType,
    19→  type PlacedAssemblage,
    20→  CHUNK_SIZE,
    21→  RENDER_RADIUS,
    22→  UNLOAD_RADIUS,
    23→  getAssemblagesByEnvironment,
    24→  ALL_ASSEMBLAGES,
    25→} from './assemblages';
    26→import { world, createEntity, removeEntity, type Entity } from '../core/ecs';
    27→
    28→// Seeded random number generator for reproducible chunk generation
    29→class SeededRandom {
    30→  private seed: number;
    31→
    32→  constructor(seed: number) {
    33→    this.seed = seed;
    34→  }
    35→
    36→  // Mulberry32 PRNG
    37→  next(): number {
    38→    let t = (this.seed += 0x6d2b79f5);
    39→    t = Math.imul(t ^ (t >>> 15), t | 1);
    40→    t ^= t + Math.imul(t ^ (t >>> 7), t | 61);
    41→    return ((t ^ (t >>> 14)) >>> 0) / 4294967296;
    42→  }
    43→
    44→  nextInt(min: number, max: number): number {
    45→    return Math.floor(this.next() * (max - min + 1)) + min;
    46→  }
    47→
    48→  pick<T>(array: T[]): T {
    49→    return array[Math.floor(this.next() * array.length)];
    50→  }
    51→
    52→  shuffle<T>(array: T[]): T[] {
    53→    const result = [...array];
    54→    for (let i = result.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
    55→      const j = Math.floor(this.next() * (i + 1));
    56→      [result[i], result[j]] = [result[j], result[i]];
    57→    }
    58→    return result;
    59→  }
    60→}
    61→
    62→// Hash function for generating chunk seeds
    63→function hashChunkCoords(x: number, z: number, worldSeed: number): number {
    64→  // Simple but effective hash combining coordinates with world seed
    65→  let hash = worldSeed;
    66→  hash = ((hash << 5) - hash + x) | 0;
    67→  hash = ((hash << 5) - hash + z) | 0;
    68→  hash = ((hash << 5) - hash + x * z) | 0;
    69→  return Math.abs(hash);
    70→}
    71→
    72→interface LoadedChunk {
    73→  x: number;
    74→  z: number;
    75→  state: ChunkState;
    76→  root: TransformNode;
    77→  entities: Entity[];
    78→  lastAccessed: number;
    79→}
    80→
    81→export class ChunkManager {
    82→  private scene: Scene;
    83→  private worldSeed: number;
    84→  private environment: EnvironmentType;
    85→  private loadedChunks: Map<string, LoadedChunk> = new Map();
    86→  private loadingChunks: Set<string> = new Set();
    87→  private playerChunkX = 0;
    88→  private playerChunkZ = 0;
    89→  private root: TransformNode;
    90→
    91→  constructor(scene: Scene, worldSeed: number, environment: EnvironmentType) {
    92→    this.scene = scene;
    93→    this.worldSeed = worldSeed;
    94→    this.environment = environment;
    95→    this.root = new TransformNode('chunkManager', scene);
    96→  }
    97→
    98→  private getChunkKey(x: number, z: number): string {
    99→    return `${x},${z}`;
   100→  }
   101→
   102→  private worldToChunk(worldPos: Vector3): { x: number; z: number } {
   103→    return {
   104→      x: Math.floor(worldPos.x / CHUNK_SIZE),
   105→      z: Math.floor(worldPos.z / CHUNK_SIZE),
   106→    };
   107→  }
   108→
   109→  /**
   110→   * Update chunk loading based on player position
   111→   */
   112→  async update(playerPosition: Vector3): Promise<void> {
   113→    const playerChunk = this.worldToChunk(playerPosition);
   114→
   115→    // Check if player has moved to a new chunk
   116→    if (playerChunk.x !== this.playerChunkX || playerChunk.z !== this.playerChunkZ) {
   117→      this.playerChunkX = playerChunk.x;
   118→      this.playerChunkZ = playerChunk.z;
   119→
   120→      // Trigger chunk loading/unloading
   121→      await this.updateLoadedChunks();
   122→    }
   123→
   124→    // Update last accessed time for chunks player is near
   125→    const nearbyKey = this.getChunkKey(playerChunk.x, playerChunk.z);
   126→    const nearbyChunk = this.loadedChunks.get(nearbyKey);
   127→    if (nearbyChunk) {
   128→      nearbyChunk.lastAccessed = Date.now();
   129→    }
   130→  }
   131→
   132→  /**
   133→   * Load chunks in render radius, unload those outside
   134→   */
   135→  private async updateLoadedChunks(): Promise<void> {
   136→    const chunksToLoad: { x: number; z: number }[] = [];
   137→    const chunksToUnload: string[] = [];
   138→
   139→    // Determine which chunks should be loaded
   140→    for (let dx = -RENDER_RADIUS; dx <= RENDER_RADIUS; dx++) {
   141→      for (let dz = -RENDER_RADIUS; dz <= RENDER_RADIUS; dz++) {
   142→        const x = this.playerChunkX + dx;
   143→        const z = this.playerChunkZ + dz;
   144→        const key = this.getChunkKey(x, z);
   145→
   146→        if (!this.loadedChunks.has(key) && !this.loadingChunks.has(key)) {
   147→          chunksToLoad.push({ x, z });
   148→        }
   149→      }
   150→    }
   151→
   152→    // Determine which chunks should be unloaded
   153→    for (const [key, chunk] of this.loadedChunks) {
   154→      const dx = Math.abs(chunk.x - this.playerChunkX);
   155→      const dz = Math.abs(chunk.z - this.playerChunkZ);
   156→
   157→      if (dx > UNLOAD_RADIUS || dz > UNLOAD_RADIUS) {
   158→        chunksToUnload.push(key);
   159→      }
   160→    }
   161→
   162→    // Unload distant chunks first (frees memory)
   163→    for (const key of chunksToUnload) {
   164→      await this.unloadChunk(key);
   165→    }
   166→
   167→    // Load new chunks (prioritize closer ones)
   168→    chunksToLoad.sort((a, b) => {
   169→      const distA = Math.abs(a.x - this.playerChunkX) + Math.abs(a.z - this.playerChunkZ);
   170→      const distB = Math.abs(b.x - this.playerChunkX) + Math.abs(b.z - this.playerChunkZ);
   171→      return distA - distB;
   172→    });
   173→
   174→    // Load chunks in batches to avoid frame drops
   175→    const BATCH_SIZE = 2;
   176→    for (let i = 0; i < Math.min(chunksToLoad.length, BATCH_SIZE); i++) {
   177→      const { x, z } = chunksToLoad[i];
   178→      await this.loadChunk(x, z);
   179→    }
   180→  }
   181→
   182→  /**
   183→   * Load a chunk - either from database or generate new
   184→   */
   185→  private async loadChunk(x: number, z: number): Promise<void> {
   186→    const key = this.getChunkKey(x, z);
   187→    if (this.loadedChunks.has(key) || this.loadingChunks.has(key)) {
   188→      return;
   189→    }
   190→
   191→    this.loadingChunks.add(key);
   192→
   193→    try {
   194→      // Check if chunk exists in database
   195→      let state = await this.loadChunkState(x, z);
   196→
   197→      if (!state) {
   198→        // Generate new chunk
   199→        state = await this.generateChunk(x, z);
   200→        // Save to database
   201→        await this.saveChunkState(state);
   202→      }
   203→
   204→      // Spawn the chunk in the scene
   205→      const loaded = await this.spawnChunk(state);
   206→      this.loadedChunks.set(key, loaded);
   207→
   208→    } catch (error) {
   209→      console.error(`Failed to load chunk ${key}:`, error);
   210→    } finally {
   211→      this.loadingChunks.delete(key);
   212→    }
   213→  }
   214→
   215→  /**
   216→   * Unload a chunk - save state and remove from scene
   217→   */
   218→  private async unloadChunk(key: string): Promise<void> {
   219→    const chunk = this.loadedChunks.get(key);
   220→    if (!chunk) return;
   221→
   222→    // Update state with current entity states
   223→    await this.updateChunkState(chunk);
   224→
   225→    // Save to database
   226→    await this.saveChunkState(chunk.state);
   227→
   228→    // Remove entities from ECS
   229→    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
   230→      removeEntity(entity);
   231→    }
   232→
   233→    // Dispose scene objects
   234→    chunk.root.dispose();
   235→
   236→    this.loadedChunks.delete(key);
   237→  }
   238→
   239→  /**
   240→   * Generate a new chunk using seeded random and assemblages
   241→   */
   242→  private async generateChunk(x: number, z: number): Promise<ChunkState> {
   243→    const seed = hashChunkCoords(x, z, this.worldSeed);
   244→    const rng = new SeededRandom(seed);
   245→
   246→    const state: ChunkState = {
   247→      chunkX: x,
   248→      chunkZ: z,
   249→      environment: this.environment,
   250→      seed,
   251→      assemblages: [],
   252→      doors: [],
   253→      loot: [],
   254→      enemies: [],
   255→      triggers: [],
   256→      firstVisited: Date.now(),
   257→      lastVisited: Date.now(),
   258→      fullyExplored: false,
   259→    };
   260→
   261→    // Get available assemblages for this environment
   262→    const available = getAssemblagesByEnvironment(this.environment);
   263→
   264→    if (available.length === 0) {
   265→      console.warn(`No assemblages for environment: ${this.environment}`);
   266→      return state;
   267→    }
   268→
   269→    // Simple generation: place assemblages based on environment type
   270→    if (this.environment === 'station_interior') {
   271→      // Interior: corridor-based layout
   272→      this.generateInteriorLayout(state, rng, available);
   273→    } else if (this.environment === 'surface_rocky') {
   274→      // Exterior: terrain with scattered features
   275→      this.generateExteriorLayout(state, rng, available);
   276→    } else if (this.environment === 'hive_organic') {
   277→      // Hive: tunnel network
   278→      this.generateHiveLayout(state, rng, available);
   279→    }
   280→
   281→    return state;
   282→  }
   283→
   284→  private generateInteriorLayout(
   285→    state: ChunkState,
   286→    rng: SeededRandom,
   287→    available: AssemblageDefinition[]
   288→  ): void {
   289→    // For interior, create a corridor network
   290→    const corridors = available.filter(a =>
   291→      a.type.startsWith('corridor') || a.type === 'airlock'
   292→    );
   293→
   294→    if (corridors.length === 0) return;
   295→
   296→    // Place 2-4 assemblages per chunk
   297→    const count = rng.nextInt(2, 4);
   298→    const gridSize = CHUNK_SIZE / 4; // 8 grid cells per chunk
   299→
   300→    for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
   301→      const assemblage = rng.pick(corridors);
   302→      const gridX = rng.nextInt(0, gridSize - assemblage.gridWidth);
   303→      const gridZ = rng.nextInt(0, gridSize - assemblage.gridDepth);
   304→      const rotation = rng.pick([0, 90, 180, 270]) as 0 | 90 | 180 | 270;
   305→
   306→      state.assemblages.push({
   307→        type: assemblage.type,
   308→        gridX,
   309→        gridZ,
   310→        rotation,
   311→        entityIds: [], // Will be filled when spawned
   312→      });
   313→    }
   314→  }
   315→
   316→  private generateExteriorLayout(
   317→    state: ChunkState,
   318→    rng: SeededRandom,
   319→    available: AssemblageDefinition[]
   320→  ): void {
   321→    // Always have base terrain
   322→    const terrains = available.filter(a => a.type.startsWith('terrain'));
   323→    if (terrains.length > 0) {
   324→      state.assemblages.push({
   325→        type: 'terrain_flat',
   326→        gridX: 0,
   327→        gridZ: 0,
   328→        rotation: 0,
   329→        entityIds: [],
   330→      });
   331→    }
   332→
   333→    // Add rock clusters randomly
   334→    const rocks = available.filter(a => a.type === 'rock_cluster');
   335→    if (rocks.length > 0) {
   336→      const rockCount = rng.nextInt(0, 5);
   337→      for (let i = 0; i < rockCount; i++) {
   338→        const gridX = rng.nextInt(0, 6);
   339→        const gridZ = rng.nextInt(0, 6);
   340→
   341→        state.assemblages.push({
   342→          type: 'rock_cluster',
   343→          gridX,
   344→          gridZ,
   345→          rotation: rng.pick([0, 90, 180, 270]) as 0 | 90 | 180 | 270,
   346→          entityIds: [],
   347→        });
   348→      }
   349→    }
   350→  }
   351→
   352→  private generateHiveLayout(
   353→    state: ChunkState,
   354→    rng: SeededRandom,
   355→    available: AssemblageDefinition[]
   356→  ): void {
   357→    const tunnels = available.filter(a =>
   358→      a.type.startsWith('tunnel') || a.type === 'egg_chamber'
   359→    );
   360→
   361→    if (tunnels.length === 0) return;
   362→
   363→    // Hives are more connected - create a branching network
   364→    const count = rng.nextInt(1, 3);
   365→    const gridSize = CHUNK_SIZE / 4;
   366→
   367→    for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
   368→      const assemblage = rng.pick(tunnels);
   369→      const gridX = rng.nextInt(0, gridSize - assemblage.gridWidth);
   370→      const gridZ = rng.nextInt(0, gridSize - assemblage.gridDepth);
   371→
   372→      state.assemblages.push({
   373→        type: assemblage.type,
   374→        gridX,
   375→        gridZ,
   376→        rotation: rng.pick([0, 90, 180, 270]) as 0 | 90 | 180 | 270,
   377→        entityIds: [],
   378→      });
   379→    }
   380→  }
   381→
   382→  /**
   383→   * Spawn chunk entities in the scene
   384→   */
   385→  private async spawnChunk(state: ChunkState): Promise<LoadedChunk> {
   386→    const chunkRoot = new TransformNode(
   387→      `chunk_${state.chunkX}_${state.chunkZ}`,
   388→      this.scene
   389→    );
   390→    chunkRoot.parent = this.root;
   391→
   392→    // Position chunk in world space
   393→    chunkRoot.position.x = state.chunkX * CHUNK_SIZE;
   394→    chunkRoot.position.z = state.chunkZ * CHUNK_SIZE;
   395→
   396→    const entities: Entity[] = [];
   397→
   398→    // Spawn each assemblage
   399→    for (const placed of state.assemblages) {
   400→      const def = ALL_ASSEMBLAGES[placed.type];
   401→      if (!def) {
   402→        console.warn(`Unknown assemblage type: ${placed.type}`);
   403→        continue;
   404→      }
   405→
   406→      // Create assemblage root
   407→      const assembRoot = new TransformNode(
   408→        `assem_${placed.type}_${placed.gridX}_${placed.gridZ}`,
   409→        this.scene
   410→      );
   411→      assembRoot.parent = chunkRoot;
   412→      assembRoot.position.x = placed.gridX * 4;
   413→      assembRoot.position.z = placed.gridZ * 4;
   414→      assembRoot.rotation.y = (placed.rotation * Math.PI) / 180;
   415→
   416→      // Spawn entities from assemblage definition
   417→      for (const entDef of def.entities) {
   418→        const entity = createEntity({
   419→          ...entDef.components,
   420→          tags: {
   421→            ...entDef.components.tags,
   422→            structural: entDef.type === 'structural',
   423→          },
   424→        });
   425→
   426→        placed.entityIds.push(entity.id);
   427→        entities.push(entity);
   428→
   429→        // TODO: Load actual mesh from modelPath
   430→        // For now, just create placeholder
   431→      }
   432→    }
   433→
   434→    return {
   435→      x: state.chunkX,
   436→      z: state.chunkZ,
   437→      state,
   438→      root: chunkRoot,
   439→      entities,
   440→      lastAccessed: Date.now(),
   441→    };
   442→  }
   443→
   444→  /**
   445→   * Update chunk state from current entity states (for persistence)
   446→   */
   447→  private async updateChunkState(chunk: LoadedChunk): Promise<void> {
   448→    chunk.state.lastVisited = Date.now();
   449→
   450→    // Update door states
   451→    chunk.state.doors = [];
   452→    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
   453→      if (entity.door) {
   454→        chunk.state.doors.push({
   455→          entityId: entity.id,
   456→          state: entity.door.state,
   457→        });
   458→      }
   459→    }
   460→
   461→    // Update enemy states
   462→    chunk.state.enemies = [];
   463→    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
   464→      if (entity.tags?.enemy && entity.health) {
   465→        chunk.state.enemies.push({
   466→          entityId: entity.id,
   467→          dead: entity.health.current <= 0,
   468→          position: entity.transform ? {
   469→            x: entity.transform.position.x,
   470→            y: entity.transform.position.y,
   471→            z: entity.transform.position.z,
   472→          } : undefined,
   473→        });
   474→      }
   475→    }
   476→
   477→    // Update loot states
   478→    chunk.state.loot = [];
   479→    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
   480→      if (entity.prop?.contents) {
   481→        chunk.state.loot.push({
   482→          entityId: entity.id,
   483→          collected: entity.prop.used,
   484→        });
   485→      }
   486→    }
   487→
   488→    // Update trigger states
   489→    chunk.state.triggers = [];
   490→    for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
   491→      if (entity.triggerZone) {
   492→        chunk.state.triggers.push({
   493→          entityId: entity.id,
   494→          triggered: entity.triggerZone.triggered,
   495→        });
   496→      }
   497→    }
   498→  }
   499→
   500→  /**
   501→   * Load chunk state from SQLite
   502→   */
   503→  private async loadChunkState(x: number, z: number): Promise<ChunkState | null> {
   504→    try {
   505→      const key = `chunk_${this.environment}_${x}_${z}`;
   506→      const data = worldDb.getChunkData(key);
   507→      if (data) {
   508→        return JSON.parse(data) as ChunkState;
   509→      }
   510→    } catch (error) {
   511→      console.warn(`Failed to load chunk state: ${error}`);
   512→    }
   513→    return null;
   514→  }
   515→
   516→  /**
   517→   * Save chunk state to SQLite
   518→   */
   519→  private async saveChunkState(state: ChunkState): Promise<void> {
   520→    try {
   521→      const key = `chunk_${this.environment}_${state.chunkX}_${state.chunkZ}`;
   522→      const data = JSON.stringify(state);
   523→      worldDb.setChunkData(key, data);
   524→    } catch (error) {
   525→      console.warn(`Failed to save chunk state: ${error}`);
   526→    }
   527→  }
   528→
   529→  /**
   530→   * Force reload all chunks (e.g., after environment change)
   531→   */
   532→  async reloadAll(): Promise<void> {
   533→    // Unload all current chunks
   534→    for (const key of [...this.loadedChunks.keys()]) {
   535→      await this.unloadChunk(key);
   536→    }
   537→
   538→    // Reload around player
   539→    await this.updateLoadedChunks();
   540→  }
   541→
   542→  /**
   543→   * Change environment type (e.g., entering hive from surface)
   544→   */
   545→  async setEnvironment(env: EnvironmentType): Promise<void> {
   546→    if (env === this.environment) return;
   547→
   548→    this.environment = env;
   549→    await this.reloadAll();
   550→  }
   551→
   552→  /**
   553→   * Get currently loaded chunk count
   554→   */
   555→  getLoadedChunkCount(): number {
   556→    return this.loadedChunks.size;
   557→  }
   558→
   559→  /**
   560→   * Dispose all resources
   561→   */
   562→  dispose(): void {
   563→    for (const chunk of this.loadedChunks.values()) {
   564→      for (const entity of chunk.entities) {
   565→        removeEntity(entity);
   566→      }
   567→      chunk.root.dispose();
   568→    }
   569→    this.loadedChunks.clear();
   570→    this.root.dispose();
   571→  }
   572→}

  // ============================================================================
  // CHUNK DATA PERSISTENCE (for ChunkManager procedural generation)
  // ============================================================================

  /**
   * Get chunk state data by key
   * @param key Format: "chunk_{environment}_{x}_{z}" e.g., "chunk_station_interior_0_1"
   * @returns JSON string of ChunkState or null if not found
   */
  getChunkData(key: string): string | null {
    if (!this.db) return null;

    const result = this.db.exec('SELECT data FROM chunk_data WHERE key = ?', [key]);

    if (result.length === 0 || result[0].values.length === 0) return null;

    return result[0].values[0][0] as string;
  }

  /**
   * Save chunk state data by key
   * @param key Format: "chunk_{environment}_{x}_{z}"
   * @param data JSON-serialized ChunkState
   */
  setChunkData(key: string, data: string): void {
    if (!this.db) return;

    this.db.run(
      `INSERT OR REPLACE INTO chunk_data (key, data, updated_at) VALUES (?, ?, ?)`,
      [key, data, Date.now()]
    );
  }

  /**
   * Delete chunk data by key
   */
  deleteChunkData(key: string): void {
    if (!this.db) return;

    this.db.run(`DELETE FROM chunk_data WHERE key = ?`, [key]);
  }

  /**
   * Get all chunk keys for a specific environment
   */
  getChunkKeysByEnvironment(environment: string): string[] {
    if (!this.db) return [];

    const result = this.db.exec(
      `SELECT key FROM chunk_data WHERE key LIKE ?`,
      [`chunk_${environment}_%`]
    );

    if (result.length === 0) return [];

    return result[0].values.map((row) => row[0] as string);
  }

  /**
   * Clear all chunk data for an environment (useful for regeneration)
   */
  clearEnvironmentChunks(environment: string): void {
    if (!this.db) return;

    this.db.run(`DELETE FROM chunk_data WHERE key LIKE ?`, [`chunk_${environment}_%`]);
  }

  /**
   * Get chunk data statistics
   */
  getChunkStats(): { totalChunks: number; byEnvironment: Record<string, number> } {
    if (!this.db) return { totalChunks: 0, byEnvironment: {} };

    const totalResult = this.db.exec('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM chunk_data');
    const total = totalResult.length > 0 ? (totalResult[0].values[0][0] as number) : 0;

    // Get counts by environment prefix
    const byEnvironment: Record<string, number> = {};
    const envResult = this.db.exec(`
      SELECT
        SUBSTR(key, 7, INSTR(SUBSTR(key, 7), '_') - 1) as env,
        COUNT(*) as count
      FROM chunk_data
      GROUP BY env
    `);

    if (envResult.length > 0) {
      for (const row of envResult[0].values) {
        const env = row[0] as string;
        const count = row[1] as number;
        if (env) {
          byEnvironment[env] = count;
        }
      }
    }

    return { totalChunks: total, byEnvironment };
  }
}

export const worldDb = new WorldDatabase();

     1→/**
     2→ * Assemblages - Pre-configured entity groups for procedural scene generation
     3→ *
     4→ * Design principles:
     5→ * 1. Each assemblage is a self-contained chunk that can be spawned/despawned
     6→ * 2. Assemblages snap to a 4-unit grid (matching PSX Mega Pack modular system)
     7→ * 3. Assemblages are serializable to SQLite for persistence
     8→ * 4. Visited locations are persisted so they don't change on revisit
     9→ */
    10→
    11→import type { Vector3 } from '@babylonjs/core/Maths/math.vector';
    12→import type { StructuralEntity } from '../components/structural';
    13→
    14→export const CHUNK_SIZE = 32; // 32 units = 8 grid tiles (4 units each)
    15→export const RENDER_RADIUS = 3; // Chunks around player to render
    16→export const UNLOAD_RADIUS = 5; // Chunks to keep in memory before unloading
    17→
    18→// ============================================================================
    19→// ASSEMBLAGE TYPES
    20→// ============================================================================
    21→
    22→export type EnvironmentType =
    23→  | 'station_interior'   // Anchor Station
    24→  | 'surface_rocky'      // Proxima surface
    25→  | 'fob_military'       // FOB Delta
    26→  | 'hive_organic'       // Chitin hive tunnels
    27→  | 'canyon'             // Canyon terrain
    28→  | 'extraction_zone';   // LZ Omega
    29→
    30→export type AssemblageType =
    31→  // Station Interior
    32→  | 'corridor_straight' | 'corridor_corner' | 'corridor_t' | 'corridor_cross'
    33→  | 'room_small' | 'room_medium' | 'room_large'
    34→  | 'hangar_bay' | 'airlock'
    35→  | 'quarters' | 'command_deck' | 'engineering'
    36→  // Surface Rocky
    37→  | 'terrain_flat' | 'terrain_rocky' | 'terrain_crater'
    38→  | 'rock_cluster' | 'boulder_field'
    39→  | 'alien_vegetation'
    40→  // FOB Military
    41→  | 'prefab_barracks' | 'prefab_command' | 'prefab_vehicle_bay'
    42→  | 'perimeter_wall' | 'perimeter_gate'
    43→  | 'comms_tower' | 'power_generator'
    44→  // Hive Organic
    45→  | 'tunnel_straight' | 'tunnel_branch' | 'tunnel_chamber'
    46→  | 'egg_chamber' | 'queen_chamber'
    47→  | 'hive_entrance'
    48→  // Common
    49→  | 'spawn_point' | 'objective_marker' | 'loot_cache';
    50→
    51→// ============================================================================
    52→// ASSEMBLAGE DEFINITION
    53→// ============================================================================
    54→
    55→export interface AssemblageConnection {
    56→  direction: 'north' | 'south' | 'east' | 'west' | 'up' | 'down';
    57→  type: 'door' | 'open' | 'wall' | 'sealed';
    58→  offset: { x: number; z: number }; // offset from chunk center in grid units
    59→}
    60→
    61→export interface AssemblageDefinition {
    62→  type: AssemblageType;
    63→  environment: EnvironmentType;
    64→
    65→  // Size in grid units (4-unit grid)
    66→  gridWidth: number;
    67→  gridDepth: number;
    68→  gridHeight: number;
    69→
    70→  // Connection points for procedural linking
    71→  connections: AssemblageConnection[];
    72→
    73→  // Entities that make up this assemblage
    74→  entities: AssemblageEntityDef[];
    75→
    76→  // Spawn configuration
    77→  enemySpawns?: { maxCount: number; types: string[]; waveDelay?: number }[];
    78→  lootSpawns?: { position: { x: number; y: number; z: number }; lootTable: string }[];
    79→
    80→  // Navigation
    81→  navmeshIncluded: boolean;
    82→  coverPoints: { x: number; y: number; z: number; direction: { x: number; z: number } }[];
    83→
    84→  // Tags for filtering
    85→  tags: string[];
    86→}
    87→
    88→export interface AssemblageEntityDef {
    89→  type: 'structural' | 'prop' | 'light' | 'door' | 'trigger' | 'spawn';
    90→  modelPath?: string;
    91→  position: { x: number; y: number; z: number };
    92→  rotation?: { x: number; y: number; z: number };
    93→  scale?: number;
    94→  components: Partial<StructuralEntity>;
    95→}
    96→
    97→// ============================================================================
    98→// CHUNK STATE FOR PERSISTENCE
    99→// ============================================================================
   100→
   101→export interface ChunkState {
   102→  chunkX: number;
   103→  chunkZ: number;
   104→  environment: EnvironmentType;
   105→
   106→  // Generation seed for reproducibility
   107→  seed: number;
   108→
   109→  // Which assemblages were placed
   110→  assemblages: PlacedAssemblage[];
   111→
   112→  // Dynamic state that persists
   113→  doors: { entityId: string; state: string }[];
   114→  loot: { entityId: string; collected: boolean }[];
   115→  enemies: { entityId: string; dead: boolean; position?: { x: number; y: number; z: number } }[];
   116→  triggers: { entityId: string; triggered: boolean }[];
   117→
   118→  // Meta
   119→  firstVisited: number; // timestamp
   120→  lastVisited: number;
   121→  fullyExplored: boolean;
   122→}
   123→
   124→export interface PlacedAssemblage {
   125→  type: AssemblageType;
   126→  gridX: number; // Position within chunk
   127→  gridZ: number;
   128→  rotation: 0 | 90 | 180 | 270;
   129→  entityIds: string[]; // IDs of spawned entities
   130→}

   582→}

   104→
   105→// Query helpers
   106→export const queries = {
   107→  players: world.with('tags', 'transform', 'health', 'velocity', 'combat'),
   108→  enemies: world.with('tags', 'transform', 'health', 'ai', 'renderable'),
   109→  allies: world.with('tags', 'transform', 'health', 'ai', 'renderable'),
   110→  projectiles: world.with('tags', 'transform', 'velocity', 'lifetime'),
   111→  renderables: world.with('transform', 'renderable'),
   112→  withHealth: world.with('health'),
   113→  withAI: world.with('ai', 'transform'),
   114→  inChunk: world.with('chunkInfo'),
   115→};

   117→// Entity factory functions
   118→export function createEntity(components: Partial<Entity>): Entity {
   119→  const entity: Entity = {
   120→    id: crypto.randomUUID(),
   121→    ...components,
   122→  };
   123→  world.add(entity);
   124→  return entity;
   125→}
   126→
   127→export function removeEntity(entity: Entity): void {
   128→  // Clean up mesh if exists
   129→  if (entity.renderable?.mesh) {
   130→    entity.renderable.mesh.dispose();
   131→  }
   132→  world.remove(entity);
   133→}
   134→
   135→/**
   136→ * Gets entities within a certain radius of a point.
   137→ * Note: This uses a 2D distance check (X/Z plane) ignoring the Y axis, ideal for gameplay logic on terrain.
   138→ */
   139→export function getEntitiesInRadius(
   140→  center: Vector3,
   141→  radius: number,
   142→  filter?: (entity: Entity) => boolean
   143→): Entity[] {
   144→  const results: Entity[] = [];
   145→  const radiusSq = radius * radius;
   146→
   147→  for (const entity of queries.renderables) {
   148→    if (!entity.transform) continue;
   149→
   150→    const dx = entity.transform.position.x - center.x;
   151→    const dz = entity.transform.position.z - center.z;
   152→    const distSq = dx * dx + dz * dz;
   153→
   154→    if (distSq <= radiusSq) {
   155→      if (!filter || filter(entity)) {
   156→        results.push(entity);
   157→      }
   158→    }
   159→  }
   160→
   161→  return results;
   162→}
   163→

    24→export class AISystem {
    25→  private entityManager: EntityManager;
    26→  private vehicles: Map<string, Vehicle> = new Map();
    27→  private playerEntity: Entity | null = null;
    28→
    29→  constructor() {
    30→    this.entityManager = new EntityManager();
    31→  }
    32→
    33→  setPlayer(player: Entity): void {
    34→    this.playerEntity = player;
    35→  }
    36→
    37→  registerEntity(entity: Entity): void {
    38→    if (!entity.transform) return;
    39→
    40→    const vehicle = new Vehicle();
    41→    vehicle.position = toYuka(entity.transform.position);
    42→    vehicle.maxSpeed = entity.velocity?.maxSpeed || 10;
    43→    vehicle.maxForce = 10;
    44→
    45→    // Set up behaviors based on entity tags
    46→    if (entity.tags?.enemy) {
    47→      // Enemies will wander until player is in range
    48→      const wander = new WanderBehavior();
    49→      wander.weight = 0.5;
    50→      vehicle.steering.add(wander);
    51→    }
    52→
    53→    this.entityManager.add(vehicle);
    54→    this.vehicles.set(entity.id, vehicle);
    55→  }
    56→
    57→  unregisterEntity(entity: Entity): void {
    58→    const vehicle = this.vehicles.get(entity.id);
    59→    if (vehicle) {
    60→      this.entityManager.remove(vehicle);
    61→      this.vehicles.delete(entity.id);
    62→    }
    63→  }
    64→
    65→  update(deltaTime: number): void {
    66→    if (!this.playerEntity?.transform) return;
    67→
    68→    const playerPos = this.playerEntity.transform.position;
    69→
    70→    // Update AI for each entity with AI component
    71→    for (const entity of queries.withAI) {
    72→      if (!entity.transform || !entity.ai) continue;
    73→
    74→      const vehicle = this.vehicles.get(entity.id);
    75→      if (!vehicle) {
    76→        this.registerEntity(entity);
    77→        continue;
    78→      }
    79→
    80→      // Sync position from Babylon to Yuka
    81→      vehicle.position = toYuka(entity.transform.position);
    82→
    83→      // Calculate distance to player
    84→      const distToPlayer = BabylonVector3.Distance(entity.transform.position, playerPos);
    85→
    86→      // Clear existing behaviors
    87→      vehicle.steering.clear();
    88→
    89→      // State machine for enemy AI
    90→      if (entity.tags?.enemy) {
    91→        if (distToPlayer < entity.ai.attackRadius) {
    92→          // Attack state - pursue and attack
    93→          entity.ai.state = 'attack';
    94→
    95→          // Reuse a shared target vehicle or update a persistent one
    96→          // For Yuka Pursuit, we need a moving target (Vehicle)
    97→          // We can create a lightweight vehicle representation of the player
    98→          const targetVehicle = new Vehicle();
    99→          targetVehicle.position = toYuka(playerPos);
   100→          // If we had player velocity, we'd set it here for better prediction
   101→          
   102→          const pursuit = new PursuitBehavior(targetVehicle);
   103→          pursuit.weight = 1.0;
   104→          vehicle.steering.add(pursuit);
   105→        } else if (distToPlayer < entity.ai.alertRadius) {
   106→          // Chase state
   107→          entity.ai.state = 'chase';
   108→
   109→          const seek = new SeekBehavior(toYuka(playerPos));
   110→          seek.weight = 1.0;
   111→          vehicle.steering.add(seek);
   112→        } else {
   113→          // Patrol state
   114→          entity.ai.state = 'patrol';
   115→
   116→          const wander = new WanderBehavior();
   117→          wander.weight = 0.5;
   118→          vehicle.steering.add(wander);
   119→        }
   120→
   121→        // Flee if health is low
   122→        if (entity.health && entity.health.current < entity.health.max * 0.2) {
   123→          entity.ai.state = 'flee';
   124→          vehicle.steering.clear();
   125→
   126→          const flee = new FleeBehavior(toYuka(playerPos));
   127→          flee.weight = 2.0;
   128→          vehicle.steering.add(flee);
   129→        }
   130→      }
   131→
   132→      // Ally AI (mechs)
   133→      if (entity.tags?.ally) {
   134→        // Find nearest enemy to attack
   135→        const nearbyEnemies = getEntitiesInRadius(
   136→          entity.transform.position,
   137→          entity.ai.alertRadius,
   138→          (e) => e.tags?.enemy === true
   139→        );
   140→
   141→        if (nearbyEnemies.length > 0) {
   142→          entity.ai.state = 'attack';
   143→          entity.ai.target = nearbyEnemies[0];
   144→
   145→          const targetPos = nearbyEnemies[0].transform?.position;
   146→          if (targetPos) {
   147→            // Keep some distance for ranged attacks
   148→            const arrive = new ArriveBehavior(toYuka(targetPos), 20);
   149→            arrive.weight = 1.0;
   150→            vehicle.steering.add(arrive);
   151→          }
   152→        } else {
   153→          // Follow player
   154→          entity.ai.state = 'support';
   155→
   156→          const arrive = new ArriveBehavior(toYuka(playerPos), 15);
   157→          arrive.weight = 0.8;
   158→          vehicle.steering.add(arrive);
   159→        }
   160→      }
   161→    }
   162→
   163→    // Update Yuka entity manager
   164→    this.entityManager.update(deltaTime);
   165→
   166→    // Sync positions back from Yuka to Babylon
   167→    for (const entity of queries.withAI) {
   168→      if (!entity.transform) continue;
   169→
   170→      const vehicle = this.vehicles.get(entity.id);
   171→      if (!vehicle) continue;
   172→
   173→      // Update entity position
   174→      entity.transform.position = toBabylon(vehicle.position);
   175→      entity.transform.position.y = 1; // Keep on ground
   176→
   177→      // Update mesh position
   178→      if (entity.renderable?.mesh) {
   179→        entity.renderable.mesh.position = entity.transform.position.clone();
   180→
   181→        // Face movement direction
   182→        if (vehicle.velocity.length() > 0.1) {
   183→          const rotation = Math.atan2(vehicle.velocity.x, vehicle.velocity.z);
   184→          entity.renderable.mesh.rotation.y = rotation;
   185→        }
   186→      }
   187→    }
   188→  }
   189→}

/Users/jbogaty/src/arcade-cabinet/stellar-descent/src/game/systems/PlayerGovernor.ts


/**
 * PlayerGovernor - Autonomous player control for e2e testing
 *
 * Uses Yuka AI behaviors to control the player character, enabling:
 * - Automated tutorial playthrough
 * - Combat engagement testing
 * - Navigation and objective completion
 * - Screenshot-based visual verification
 *
 * This is essentially a "bot player" that can exercise the full game loop.
 */

import { Vector3 as BabylonVector3 } from '@babylonjs/core/Maths/math.vector';
import {
  ArriveBehavior,
  EntityManager,
  SeekBehavior,
  Vehicle,
  Vector3 as YukaVector3,
} from 'yuka';
import type { Entity } from '../core/ecs';
import { getEntitiesInRadius } from '../core/ecs';

// Convert between Babylon and Yuka vectors
function toYuka(v: BabylonVector3): YukaVector3 {
  return new YukaVector3(v.x, v.y, v.z);
}

function toBabylon(v: YukaVector3): BabylonVector3 {
  return new BabylonVector3(v.x, v.y, v.z);
}

// High-level goals the governor can pursue
export type GovernorGoal =
  | { type: 'idle' }
  | { type: 'navigate'; target: BabylonVector3; threshold?: number }
  | { type: 'follow_objective' } // Follow current game objective
  | { type: 'engage_enemies'; aggressive?: boolean }
  | { type: 'advance_dialogue' } // Press space to advance comms
  | { type: 'interact'; targetId?: string } // Interact with nearest interactable
  | { type: 'complete_tutorial' }
  | { type: 'wait'; duration: number; started?: number };

// Events the governor can emit for test verification
export type GovernorEvent =
  | { type: 'goal_started'; goal: GovernorGoal }
  | { type: 'goal_completed'; goal: GovernorGoal }
  | { type: 'enemy_engaged'; enemyId: string }
  | { type: 'enemy_killed'; enemyId: string }
  | { type: 'damage_taken'; amount: number }
  | { type: 'position_reached'; position: BabylonVector3 }
  | { type: 'dialogue_advanced' }
  | { type: 'interaction_performed'; targetId: string }
  | { type: 'objective_updated'; objectiveText: string };

export interface GovernorConfig {
  // Movement
  moveSpeed: number;
  arrivalThreshold: number;

  // Combat
  autoShoot: boolean;
  engagementRange: number;
  fleeHealthThreshold: number;

  // Dialogue
  dialogueAdvanceDelay: number; // ms between space presses
  autoAdvanceDialogue: boolean;

  // Testing
  logActions: boolean;
  captureScreenshots: boolean;
  screenshotInterval: number; // ms
}

const DEFAULT_CONFIG: GovernorConfig = {
  moveSpeed: 8,
  arrivalThreshold: 2,
  autoShoot: true,
  engagementRange: 30,
  fleeHealthThreshold: 0.2,
  dialogueAdvanceDelay: 1500,
  autoAdvanceDialogue: true,
  logActions: true,
  captureScreenshots: false,
  screenshotInterval: 2000,
};

export class PlayerGovernor {
  private entityManager: EntityManager;
  private vehicle: Vehicle;
  private playerEntity: Entity | null = null;
  private config: GovernorConfig;

  private currentGoal: GovernorGoal = { type: 'idle' };
  private goalQueue: GovernorGoal[] = [];
  private eventListeners: ((event: GovernorEvent) => void)[] = [];

  // State tracking
  private lastDialogueAdvance = 0;
  private lastShot = 0;
  private lastScreenshot = 0;
  private inputState: {
    moveForward: boolean;
    moveBack: boolean;
    moveLeft: boolean;
    moveRight: boolean;
    shoot: boolean;
    interact: boolean;
    advanceDialogue: boolean;
  } = {
    moveForward: false,
    moveBack: false,
    moveLeft: false,
    moveRight: false,
    shoot: false,
    interact: false,
    advanceDialogue: false,
  };

  // Tutorial step tracking
  private tutorialStepsCompleted: string[] = [];
  private currentObjective: string = '';

  constructor(config: Partial<GovernorConfig> = {}) {
    this.config = { ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, ...config };
    this.entityManager = new EntityManager();
    this.vehicle = new Vehicle();
    this.vehicle.maxSpeed = this.config.moveSpeed;
    this.vehicle.maxForce = 15;
    this.entityManager.add(this.vehicle);
  }

  setPlayer(player: Entity): void {
    this.playerEntity = player;
    if (player.transform) {
      this.vehicle.position = toYuka(player.transform.position);
    }
    this.log('Player entity assigned');
  }

  addEventListener(listener: (event: GovernorEvent) => void): void {
    this.eventListeners.push(listener);
  }

  removeEventListener(listener: (event: GovernorEvent) => void): void {
    const index = this.eventListeners.indexOf(listener);
    if (index >= 0) {
      this.eventListeners.splice(index, 1);
    }
  }

  private emit(event: GovernorEvent): void {
    for (const listener of this.eventListeners) {
      listener(event);
    }
    if (this.config.logActions) {
      this.log(`Event: ${event.type}`);
    }
  }

  private log(message: string): void {
    if (this.config.logActions) {
      console.log(`[PlayerGovernor] ${message}`);
    }
  }

  // ============================================================================
  // GOAL MANAGEMENT
  // ============================================================================

  setGoal(goal: GovernorGoal): void {
    this.currentGoal = goal;
    this.emit({ type: 'goal_started', goal });
    this.log(`Goal set: ${goal.type}`);
    this.updateBehaviors();
  }

  queueGoal(goal: GovernorGoal): void {
    this.goalQueue.push(goal);
    this.log(`Goal queued: ${goal.type}`);
  }

  clearGoals(): void {
    this.currentGoal = { type: 'idle' };
    this.goalQueue = [];
    this.vehicle.steering.clear();
    this.log('Goals cleared');
  }

  private completeCurrentGoal(): void {
    this.emit({ type: 'goal_completed', goal: this.currentGoal });
    this.log(`Goal completed: ${this.currentGoal.type}`);

    // Move to next goal in queue
    if (this.goalQueue.length > 0) {
      const nextGoal = this.goalQueue.shift()!;
      this.setGoal(nextGoal);
    } else {
      this.currentGoal = { type: 'idle' };
      this.vehicle.steering.clear();
    }
  }

  // ============================================================================
  // BEHAVIOR SETUP
  // ============================================================================

  private updateBehaviors(): void {
    this.vehicle.steering.clear();

    switch (this.currentGoal.type) {
      case 'navigate':
        this.setupNavigateBehavior(this.currentGoal.target);
        break;

      case 'follow_objective':
        // Will be handled dynamically based on current objective
        break;

      case 'engage_enemies':
        // Handled in update loop
        break;

      case 'complete_tutorial':
        // Multi-phase goal handled in update
        break;

      case 'idle':
      case 'advance_dialogue':
      case 'wait':
      case 'interact':
        // No movement behavior needed
        break;
    }
  }

  private setupNavigateBehavior(target: BabylonVector3): void {
    const arrive = new ArriveBehavior(toYuka(target), 3);
    arrive.weight = 1.0;
    this.vehicle.steering.add(arrive);
  }

  // ============================================================================
  // UPDATE LOOP
  // ============================================================================

  update(deltaTime: number): void {
    if (!this.playerEntity?.transform) return;

    const now = Date.now();

    // Sync vehicle position from player
    this.vehicle.position = toYuka(this.playerEntity.transform.position);

    // Reset input state
    this.inputState = {
      moveForward: false,
      moveBack: false,
      moveLeft: false,
      moveRight: false,
      shoot: false,
      interact: false,
      advanceDialogue: false,
    };

    // Process current goal
    switch (this.currentGoal.type) {
      case 'navigate':
        this.processNavigateGoal(this.currentGoal);
        break;

      case 'engage_enemies':
        this.processEngageEnemiesGoal(this.currentGoal);
        break;

      case 'advance_dialogue':
        this.processAdvanceDialogueGoal(now);
        break;

      case 'wait':
        this.processWaitGoal(this.currentGoal, now);
        break;

      case 'complete_tutorial':
        this.processTutorialGoal(now);
        break;

      case 'follow_objective':
        this.processFollowObjectiveGoal();
        break;

      case 'interact':
        this.processInteractGoal();
        break;

      case 'idle':
        // Do nothing
        break;
    }

    // Auto advance dialogue if enabled
    if (
      this.config.autoAdvanceDialogue &&
      this.currentGoal.type !== 'advance_dialogue' &&
      now - this.lastDialogueAdvance > this.config.dialogueAdvanceDelay
    ) {
      // Check if dialogue is visible (this would need DOM access in actual impl)
      // For now, just mark for potential advancement
    }

    // Update Yuka
    this.entityManager.update(deltaTime);

    // Apply movement from vehicle velocity
    this.applyVehicleMovement();

    // Screenshots
    if (
      this.config.captureScreenshots &&
      now - this.lastScreenshot > this.config.screenshotInterval
    ) {
      this.lastScreenshot = now;
      // Screenshot capture would be handled by the test framework
    }
  }

  private processNavigateGoal(goal: { type: 'navigate'; target: BabylonVector3; threshold?: number }): void {
    const threshold = goal.threshold ?? this.config.arrivalThreshold;
    const distance = BabylonVector3.Distance(
      this.playerEntity!.transform!.position,
      goal.target
    );

    if (distance <= threshold) {
      this.emit({ type: 'position_reached', position: goal.target });
      this.completeCurrentGoal();
    }
  }

  private processEngageEnemiesGoal(goal: { type: 'engage_enemies'; aggressive?: boolean }): void {
    const enemies = getEntitiesInRadius(
      this.playerEntity!.transform!.position,
      this.config.engagementRange,
      (e) => e.tags?.enemy === true && (e.health?.current ?? 0) > 0
    );

    if (enemies.length === 0) {
      // No enemies in range - goal complete or wander
      if (goal.aggressive) {
        // Stay aggressive, but no enemies nearby
      } else {
        this.completeCurrentGoal();
      }
      return;
    }

    // Target nearest enemy
    const nearest = enemies.reduce((closest, enemy) => {
      const distToEnemy = BabylonVector3.Distance(
        this.playerEntity!.transform!.position,
        enemy.transform!.position
      );
      const distToClosest = BabylonVector3.Distance(
        this.playerEntity!.transform!.position,
        closest.transform!.position
      );
      return distToEnemy < distToClosest ? enemy : closest;
    });

    // Navigate towards enemy
    const seek = new SeekBehavior(toYuka(nearest.transform!.position));
    seek.weight = 1.0;
    this.vehicle.steering.clear();
    this.vehicle.steering.add(seek);

    // Shoot if in range
    const distToTarget = BabylonVector3.Distance(
      this.playerEntity!.transform!.position,
      nearest.transform!.position
    );

    if (distToTarget < 20 && this.config.autoShoot) {
      this.inputState.shoot = true;
      this.emit({ type: 'enemy_engaged', enemyId: nearest.id });
    }
  }

  private processAdvanceDialogueGoal(now: number): void {
    if (now - this.lastDialogueAdvance > this.config.dialogueAdvanceDelay) {
      this.inputState.advanceDialogue = true;
      this.lastDialogueAdvance = now;
      this.emit({ type: 'dialogue_advanced' });
      this.completeCurrentGoal();
    }
  }

  private processWaitGoal(goal: { type: 'wait'; duration: number; started?: number }, now: number): void {
    if (!goal.started) {
      goal.started = now;
    }

    if (now - goal.started >= goal.duration) {
      this.completeCurrentGoal();
    }
  }

  private processTutorialGoal(now: number): void {
    // Tutorial has multiple phases:
    // 1. Wait for initial comms
    // 2. Advance through dialogue
    // 3. Move to waypoints
    // 4. Interact with objects
    // 5. Complete objectives

    // This is a meta-goal that queues sub-goals
    // For now, just advance dialogue
    if (now - this.lastDialogueAdvance > this.config.dialogueAdvanceDelay) {
      this.inputState.advanceDialogue = true;
      this.lastDialogueAdvance = now;
      this.emit({ type: 'dialogue_advanced' });
    }
  }

  private processFollowObjectiveGoal(): void {
    // Would need to parse current objective and navigate/interact accordingly
    // For now, just idle
  }

  private processInteractGoal(): void {
    this.inputState.interact = true;
    this.completeCurrentGoal();
  }

  private applyVehicleMovement(): void {
    // Convert Yuka velocity to input state
    const velocity = this.vehicle.velocity;

    if (velocity.length() > 0.1) {
      // Determine primary movement direction
      const normalized = velocity.clone().normalize();

      if (normalized.z < -0.3) this.inputState.moveForward = true;
      if (normalized.z > 0.3) this.inputState.moveBack = true;
      if (normalized.x < -0.3) this.inputState.moveLeft = true;
      if (normalized.x > 0.3) this.inputState.moveRight = true;
    }
  }

  // ============================================================================
  // INPUT STATE ACCESS (for game input system to read)
  // ============================================================================

  getInputState(): typeof this.inputState {
    return { ...this.inputState };
  }

  isMovingForward(): boolean {
    return this.inputState.moveForward;
  }

  isMovingBack(): boolean {
    return this.inputState.moveBack;
  }

  isMovingLeft(): boolean {
    return this.inputState.moveLeft;
  }

  isMovingRight(): boolean {
    return this.inputState.moveRight;
  }

  isShooting(): boolean {
    return this.inputState.shoot;
  }

  shouldAdvanceDialogue(): boolean {
    return this.inputState.advanceDialogue;
  }

  shouldInteract(): boolean {
    return this.inputState.interact;
  }

  // ============================================================================
  // UTILITY METHODS
  // ============================================================================

  getCurrentGoal(): GovernorGoal {
    return this.currentGoal;
  }

  getQueuedGoals(): GovernorGoal[] {
    return [...this.goalQueue];
  }

  getVehiclePosition(): BabylonVector3 {
    return toBabylon(this.vehicle.position);
  }

  getVehicleVelocity(): BabylonVector3 {
    return toBabylon(this.vehicle.velocity);
  }

  setObjective(objective: string): void {
    this.currentObjective = objective;
    this.emit({ type: 'objective_updated', objectiveText: objective });
    this.log(`Objective updated: ${objective}`);
  }

  markTutorialStepComplete(step: string): void {
    if (!this.tutorialStepsCompleted.includes(step)) {
      this.tutorialStepsCompleted.push(step);
      this.log(`Tutorial step completed: ${step}`);
    }
  }

  // ============================================================================
  // PRESET GOAL SEQUENCES
  // ============================================================================

  /**
   * Run a full tutorial playthrough
   */
  runTutorialPlaythrough(): void {
    this.clearGoals();

    // Queue tutorial sequence
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'wait', duration: 2000 }); // Wait for game to load
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'advance_dialogue' }); // First comms
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'wait', duration: 1000 });
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'advance_dialogue' });
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'wait', duration: 1000 });
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'advance_dialogue' });
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'wait', duration: 1000 });
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'advance_dialogue' });
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'wait', duration: 1000 });
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'advance_dialogue' });
    this.queueGoal({ type: 'follow_objective' }); // Start following objectives

    // Start first goal
    if (this.goalQueue.length > 0) {
      const firstGoal = this.goalQueue.shift()!;
      this.setGoal(firstGoal);
    }

    this.log('Tutorial playthrough started');
  }

  /**
   * Navigate to a specific position
   */
  navigateTo(position: BabylonVector3, threshold?: number): void {
    this.setGoal({ type: 'navigate', target: position, threshold });
  }

  /**
   * Engage all enemies in range
   */
  engageEnemies(aggressive = false): void {
    this.setGoal({ type: 'engage_enemies', aggressive });
  }

  /**
   * Wait for a duration then continue
   */
  wait(duration: number): void {
    this.setGoal({ type: 'wait', duration });
  }

  dispose(): void {
    this.entityManager.clear();
    this.eventListeners = [];
    this.log('Governor disposed');
  }
}

// Singleton for easy access in tests
let governorInstance: PlayerGovernor | null = null;

export function getPlayerGovernor(config?: Partial<GovernorConfig>): PlayerGovernor {
  if (!governorInstance) {
    governorInstance = new PlayerGovernor(config);
  }
  return governorInstance;
}

export function resetPlayerGovernor(): void {
  if (governorInstance) {
    governorInstance.dispose();
    governorInstance = null;
  }
}

   224→  private applyCurvature(mesh: Mesh, subdivisions: number): void {
   225→    const positions = mesh.getVerticesData('position');
   226→    if (!positions) return;
   227→
   228→    const newPositions = new Float32Array(positions.length);
   229→
   230→    for (let i = 0; i < positions.length; i += 3) {
   231→      const x = positions[i];
   232→      const y = positions[i + 1];
   233→      const z = positions[i + 2];
   234→
   235→      // Calculate distance from center
   236→      const distSq = x * x + z * z;
   237→
   238→      // Apply spherical curvature - drop height based on distance from center
   239→      // This simulates standing on a sphere where distant points curve away
   240→      const curvatureDrop = distSq * CURVATURE_SCALE;
   241→
   242→      newPositions[i] = x;
   243→      newPositions[i + 1] = y - curvatureDrop;
   244→      newPositions[i + 2] = z;
   245→    }
   246→
   247→    mesh.updateVerticesData('position', newPositions);
   248→    mesh.createNormals(true);
   249→  }

    47→  precision highp float;
    48→

    50→  varying vec3 vNormal;
    51→  varying vec2 vUV;
    52→  varying float vDistanceFromPlayer;

    56→
    57→  // Simple noise for terrain variation
    58→  float hash(vec2 p) {
    59→    return fract(sin(dot(p, vec2(127.1, 311.7))) * 43758.5453);
    60→  }
    61→
    62→  float noise(vec2 p) {
    63→    vec2 i = floor(p);
    64→    vec2 f = fract(p);
    65→    f = f * f * (3.0 - 2.0 * f);
    66→
    67→    float a = hash(i);
    68→    float b = hash(i + vec2(1.0, 0.0));
    69→    float c = hash(i + vec2(0.0, 1.0));
    70→    float d = hash(i + vec2(1.0, 1.0));
    71→
    72→    return mix(mix(a, b, f.x), mix(c, d, f.x), f.y);
    73→  }
    74→
    75→  float fbm(vec2 p) {
    76→    float value = 0.0;
    77→    float amplitude = 0.5;
    78→    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    79→      value += amplitude * noise(p);
    80→      p *= 2.0;
    81→      amplitude *= 0.5;
    82→    }
    83→    return value;
    84→  }
    85→
    86→  void main() {
    87→    // Base terrain color - reddish brown alien rock
    88→    vec3 baseColor = vec3(0.55, 0.4, 0.3);
    89→
    90→    // Add texture
    91→    vec3 texColor = texture2D(rockTexture, vUV * 50.0).rgb;
    92→
    93→    // Add noise-based variation for different terrain regions
    94→    float terrainNoise = fbm(vPosition.xz * 0.001);
    95→    vec3 color1 = vec3(0.6, 0.45, 0.35); // Lighter rock
    96→    vec3 color2 = vec3(0.4, 0.3, 0.25);  // Darker rock
    97→    vec3 color3 = vec3(0.7, 0.5, 0.3);   // Rusty orange
    98→
    99→    vec3 terrainColor = mix(color1, color2, terrainNoise);
   100→    terrainColor = mix(terrainColor, color3, fbm(vPosition.xz * 0.003));
   101→
   102→    // Combine with texture
   103→    vec3 finalColor = mix(terrainColor, texColor * terrainColor, 0.5);
   104→
   105→    // Lighting
   106→    float NdotL = max(dot(vNormal, sunDirection), 0.0);
   107→    float ambient = 0.25;
   108→    float diffuse = NdotL * 0.75;
   109→
   110→    finalColor *= (ambient + diffuse);
   111→
   112→    // Distance fade to atmosphere color
   113→    float atmosphereFade = smoothstep(500.0, 5000.0, vDistanceFromPlayer);
   114→    vec3 atmosphereColor = vec3(0.35, 0.25, 0.2); // Dusty atmosphere
   115→    finalColor = mix(finalColor, atmosphereColor, atmosphereFade * 0.6);
   116→
   117→    gl_FragColor = vec4(finalColor, 1.0);
   118→  }
   119→`;

   137→const planetFragmentShader = `
   138→  precision highp float;
   139→

   141→  varying vec3 vNormal;
   142→  varying vec2 vUV;
   143→
   144→  uniform vec3 sunDirection;
   145→  uniform vec3 cameraPosition;
   146→  uniform sampler2D surfaceTexture;
   147→
   148→  float hash(vec2 p) {
   149→    return fract(sin(dot(p, vec2(127.1, 311.7))) * 43758.5453);
   150→  }
   151→
   152→  float noise(vec2 p) {
   153→    vec2 i = floor(p);
   154→    vec2 f = fract(p);
   155→    f = f * f * (3.0 - 2.0 * f);
   156→    return mix(mix(hash(i), hash(i + vec2(1.0, 0.0)), f.x),
   157→               mix(hash(i + vec2(0.0, 1.0)), hash(i + vec2(1.0, 1.0)), f.x), f.y);
   158→  }
   159→
   160→  float fbm(vec2 p) {
   161→    float v = 0.0;
   162→    float a = 0.5;
   163→    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
   164→      v += a * noise(p);
   165→      p *= 2.0;
   166→      a *= 0.5;
   167→    }
   168→    return v;
   169→  }
   170→
   171→  void main() {

    43→  precision highp float;

    45→  uniform float time;
    46→
    47→  float hash(vec3 p) {
    48→    p = fract(p * 0.3183099 + 0.1);
    49→    p *= 17.0;
    50→    return fract(p.x * p.y * p.z * (p.x + p.y + p.z));
    51→  }
    52→
    53→  float stars(vec3 ray) {
    54→    vec3 p = ray * 300.0;
    55→    float brightness = 0.0;
    56→
    57→    for (float i = 0.0; i < 3.0; i++) {
    58→      vec3 q = fract(p) - 0.5;
    59→      vec3 id = floor(p);
    60→      float h = hash(id);
    61→
    62→      float size = 0.02 + h * 0.03;
    63→      float star = smoothstep(size, 0.0, length(q));
    64→      float twinkle = 0.7 + 0.3 * sin(time * (2.0 + h * 4.0) + h * 6.28);
    65→      brightness += star * twinkle * (0.5 + h * 0.5);
    66→      p *= 2.1;
    67→    }
    68→
    69→    return brightness;
    70→  }
    71→
    72→  float nebula(vec3 ray) {
    73→    float n = 0.0;
    74→    vec3 p = ray * 2.0;
    75→
    76→    for (float i = 0.0; i < 4.0; i++) {
    77→      float h = hash(floor(p));
    78→      n += h * smoothstep(0.8, 0.2, length(fract(p) - 0.5));
    79→      p *= 2.0;
    80→    }
    81→
    82→    return n * 0.15;
    83→  }
    84→
    85→  void main() {

Assistant2026-01-30T03:37:40.196Z


Thinking
I found the problem! Look at the shader dump - after the shader defines, there's HTML code getting injected:


#define SHADER_NAME vertex:default
precision highp float;
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
...



The HTML is being injected into the shader! This is happening because Babylon.js is trying to fetch a shader file using something like fetch('/somefile') and the dev server is returning the HTML page (index.html) instead of the shader file due to a 404.


The shader code includes <!DOCTYPE html> which explains the < character at line 51 (after all the #defines).


This is happening with the default shader (StandardMaterial's shader) which means Babylon.js is unable to find its built-in shaders. This is a tree-shaking issue - the StandardMaterial shaders aren't being included properly.


Let me check if there's a missing import for StandardMaterial shaders.


Assistant2026-01-30T03:37:41.372Z

  • The dev server was returning index.html instead of shader code, causing VERTEX SHADER ERROR: '<' : syntax error
    • 

  • Fix: Added imports for @babylonjs/core/Shaders/default.vertex and @babylonjs/core/Shaders/default.fragment
    • 

  • Also added @babylonjs/core/Animations/animatable import for scene.beginAnimation
    •
